{"title_page": "Tsunami warning system", "text_new": "EAT MY POO DDI.Oregon.JPG|thumb|300px|Evacuation route sign in a low-lying coastal area on the West Coast of the United States]]\nA '''tsunami warning system''' ('''TWS''') is used to detect [[tsunami]]s in advance and issue warnings to prevent loss of life and damage to property. It is made up of two equally important components: a EAT MY POOnetwork of sensors to detect tsunamis and a communications infrastructure to issue timely alarms to permit evacuation of the coastal areas.  There are two distinct types of tsunami warning systems: '''international''' and '''regional'''.  When operating, seismic alerts are used to instigate the watches and warnings; then, data from observed sea level height (either shore-based tide gauges or [[Deep-ocean Assessment and Reporting of Tsunamis|DART]] buoys) are used to verify the existence of a tsunami.  Other systems have been proposed to augment the warning procedures; for example, it has been suggested that the duration and frequency content of [[T wave (seismic)|t-wave]] energy (which is earthquake energy trapped in the ocean [[SOFAR channel]]) is indicative of an earthquake's tsunami potential.<ref>Salzberg, 2006</ref>\n\n==History and forecasting==\n{{unreferenced|section|date=June 2017}}\nThe first rudimentary system to alert communities of an impending tsunami was attempted in [[Hawaii]] in the 1920s. More advanced systems were developed in the wake of the April 1, 1946 (caused by the [[1946 Aleutian Islands earthquake]]) and May 23, 1960 (caused by the [[1960 Valdivia earthquake]]) tsunamis which caused massive devastation in [[Hilo, Hawaii]].  While tsunamis travel at between 500 and 1,000&nbsp;km/h (around 0.14 and 0.28&nbsp;km/s) in open water, earthquakes can be detected almost at once as [[seismic wave]]s travel with a typical speed of 4&nbsp;km/s (around 14,400&nbsp;km/h).  This gives time for a possible tsunami forecast to be made and warnings to be issued to threatened areas, if warranted.  Until a reliable model is able to predict which earthquakes will produce significant tsunamis, this approach will produce many more false alarms than verified warnings.\n\n==International  systems (IS)==\n\n===Pacific Ocean===\n[[File:TsunamiHazardSign.svg|right|thumb|Japanese Tsunami warning sign]]\nTsunami warnings ([[Specific Area Message Encoding|SAME]] code:  '''TSW''') for most of the [[Pacific Ocean]] are issued by the [[Pacific Tsunami Warning Center]] (PTWC), operated by the [[United States]] [[NOAA]] in [[Ewa Beach, Hawaii]]. NOAA's [[National Tsunami Warning Center]] (NTWC) in [[Palmer, Alaska]] issues warnings for North America, including Alaska, British Columbia, Oregon, California, the Gulf of Mexico, and the East coast. The PTWC was established in 1949, following the 1946 [[Aleutian Island earthquake]] and a tsunami that resulted in 165 casualties on Hawaii and in Alaska; NTWC was founded in 1967. International coordination is achieved through the International Coordination Group for the Tsunami Warning System in the Pacific, established by the [[Intergovernmental Oceanographic Commission]] of [[UNESCO]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ioc.unesco.org/itsu/ |title=IOC Oceans &#124; United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization |publisher=Ioc.unesco.org |date= |accessdate=2018-10-02}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, The US congressional panel passed a vote to continue funding a global tsunami detection system that gives U.S. officials an accurate forecast in order to decrease damage cause by Tsunamis.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.virginislandsdailynews.com/ap/threatened-by-trump-s-budget-tsunami-warning-system-gets-backing/article_7ab750c2-46dd-57b5-8d51-711f2435e6b5.html|title=Threatened by Trump's budget, tsunami warning system gets backing from congressional panel|last=Times|first=Los Angeles|work=The Virgin Islands Daily News|access-date=2017-07-18|language=en}}</ref>\n\n===Indian Ocean (ICG/IOTWMS)===\n{{main article|Indian Ocean Tsunami Warning System}}\n\n[[File:Tsunami-warning-centre hikkaduwa sri-lanka.jpg|right|thumb|Tsunami Early Warning Tower board in Hikkaduwa, Sri Lanka]]\n\nAfter the [[2004 Indian Ocean earthquake|2004 Indian Ocean Tsunami]] which killed almost 250,000 people, a [[United Nations]] conference was held in January 2005 in [[Kobe]], [[Japan]], and decided that as an initial step towards an [[International Early Warning Programme]], the UN should establish an [[Indian Ocean Tsunami Warning System]]. This resulted in a warning system for Indonesia and other affected areas. Indonesia's system fell out of service in 2012 because the detection buoys were no longer operational. Tsunami prediction is therefore currently limited to detection of seismic activity; there is no system to predict tsunamis based on volcanic eruptions.\n\nIndonesia was hit by tsunamis in [[2018 Sulawesi earthquake and tsunami|September]] and [[2018 Sunda Strait tsunami|December]] 2018. The December 2018 tsunami was caused by a volcano.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2018/12/24/asia/indonesia-tsunami-disaster-year-intl/index.html|title=How Indonesia's tsunami warning system failed its citizens again|last=Griffiths|first=James|date=24 December 2018|work=CNN|access-date=24 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n===North Eastern Atlantic, the Mediterranean and Connected Seas (ICG/NEAMTWS)===\nThe First United Session of the Inter-governmental Coordination Group for the Tsunami Early Warning and Mitigation System in the North Eastern Atlantic, the Mediterranean and connected Seas (ICG/NEAMTWS), established by the [[Intergovernmental Oceanographic Commission]] of [[UNESCO]] Assembly during its 23rd Session in June 2005, through Resolution XXIII.14, took place in [[Rome]] on 21 and 22 November 2005.\n\nThe meeting, hosted by the Government of Italy (the [[Italian Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] and the [[Ministry of the Environment (Italy)|Italian Ministry for the Environment and Protection of Land and Sea]]), was attended by more than 150 participants from 24 countries, 13 organizations and numerous observers.\n\n===Caribbean===\n\nA Caribbean-wide tsunami warning system was planned to be instituted by the year 2010, by representatives of [[Caribbean Community|Caribbean nations]] who met in [[Panama City]] in March 2008. [[Panama]]'s last major tsunami killed 4,500 people in 1882.<ref>[http://uk.reuters.com/article/environmentNews/idUKN1332624020080313 Reuters:Caribbean plans tsunami warning system by 2010]</ref> [[Barbados]] has said it will review or test its tsunami protocol in February 2010 as a regional pilot.<ref>{{cite news\n  |title=Time right to test disaster awareness system |author=\n  |first=Carol |last=Martindale\n  |url=http://www.nationnews.com/news/local/tsunami-protocol-in-full-effect-copy-for-web\n  |newspaper=[[The Daily Nation (Barbados)|Nation Newspaper]]\n  |date=24 January 2010 |page= |pages= |at= |accessdate=24 January 2010\n  |quote=A TSUNAMI PROTOCOL to be tested here next month will help Barbadians be better prepared to deal with natural disasters such as earthquakes. ... Harewood said Barbados was nominated and accepted as the \"pilot state\" for the tsunami protocol which will be discussed from February 22 to 26.  He said the objective of the Standard Operational Procedure and Communications Protocol, which has been being worked on for the last two years, is to provide more information on what must be done in the event of a tsunami, earthquake or any other major disaster.  He noted that one of the things they would be doing was adopting a general public service announcement through the Government Information Service (GIS) to help increase awareness of tsunamis.\n}}</ref>{{update after|2014|7}}\n\n==Regional warning systems==\n[[File:1 Tsunamiwarnsystem in Dili.jpg|thumb|Tsunami warning system in [[East Timor]]]]\n\nRegional (or local) warning system centers use [[seismic]] data about nearby recent earthquakes to determine if there is a possible local threat of a tsunami. Such systems are capable of issuing warnings to the general public (via public address systems and sirens) in less than 15 minutes. Although the [[epicenter]] and [[moment magnitude scale|moment magnitude]] of an underwater quake and the probable tsunami arrival times can be quickly calculated, it is almost always impossible to know whether underwater ground shifts have occurred which will result in tsunami waves. As a result, false alarms can occur with these systems, but the disruption is small, which makes sense due to the highly localized nature of these extremely quick warnings, in combination with how difficult it would be for a false alarm to affect more than a small area of the system. Real tsunamis would affect more than just a small portion.\n{{Citation needed|date=April 2011}}\n\n===Japan===\nJapan has a nationwide tsunami warning system. The system usually issues the warning minutes after an [[Earthquake Early Warning (Japan)|Earthquake Early Warning]] (EEW) is issued, should there be expected waves.<ref>{{cite web|title=Japan Meteorological Agency\uff5cFlow of issuance of information about tsunami and earthquake|url=http://www.data.jma.go.jp/svd/eqev/data/en/guide/info.html|accessdate=15 April 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"2011warning\">{{cite web|title=80 Seconds of Warning for Tokyo|url=https://www.technologyreview.com/s/423274/80-seconds-of-warning-for-tokyo/|website=MIT Technology Review|accessdate=15 April 2016}}</ref> The tsunami warning was issued within 3 minutes with the most serious rating on its warning scale during the [[2011 T\u014dhoku earthquake and tsunami]]; it was rated as a \"major tsunami\", being at least 3&nbsp;m (9.8&nbsp;ft) high.<ref name=\"2011warning\"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Emergency Warning System Starting Shortly|url=http://www.jma.go.jp/jma/en/Emergency_Warning/Leaflet(Emergency_Warning).pdf|accessdate=15 April 2016}}</ref> An improved system was unveiled on March 7, 2013 following the 2011 disaster to better access the waves.<ref>{{cite web|title=Leaflet \"Start of New Tsunami Warning System Operation\"|url=http://www.data.jma.go.jp/svd/eqev/data/en/tsunami/tsunamiwarning-leaflet.pdf|accessdate=15 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Tsunami two years on: Japan finally gets warning system that would have saved hundreds of lives|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/japan/9920042/Tsunami-two-years-on-Japan-finally-gets-warning-system-that-would-have-saved-hundreds-of-lives.html|accessdate=15 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Conveying the warning==\n{{unreferenced|section|date=June 2017}}\n[[File:Okumatsushima tsunami P1130317 rotated.jpg|thumb|Mast with warning system, and sign detailing escape routes, on the coast of [[Okumatsushima]], [[Miyagi Prefecture|Miyagi]] prefecture, [[Japan]] (this coast was severely hit by the [[2011 T\u014dhoku earthquake and tsunami|2011 tsunami]])]]\nDetection and prediction of tsunamis is only half the work of the system. Of equal importance is the ability to warn the populations of the areas that will be affected. All tsunami warning systems feature multiple lines of communications (such as [[Cell Broadcast]], [[SMS]], [[e-mail]], [[fax]], [[radio]], texting and [[teleprinter|telex]], often using hardened dedicated systems) {{citation needed|date=November 2019}} enabling emergency messages to be sent to the [[emergency service]]s and [[armed forces]], as well to population-alerting systems (e.g. [[siren (noisemaker)|sirens]]) and systems like the [[Emergency Alert System]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=UNESCO |url=http://itic.ioc-unesco.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=category&id=1437&Itemid=1437 |website=International Tsunami Information Center |accessdate=5 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Shortcomings==\n{{unreferenced|section|date=June 2017}}\nWith the speed at which tsunami waves travel through open water, no system can protect against a very sudden tsunami, where the coast in question is too close to the [[epicenter]]. A devastating tsunami occurred off the coast of [[Hokkaid\u014d]] in Japan as a result of [[1993 Hokkaid\u014d earthquake|an earthquake on July 12, 1993]]. As a result, 202 people on the small island of [[Okushiri, Hokkaido]] lost their lives, and hundreds more were missing or injured. {{citation needed|date=November 2019}} This tsunami struck just three to five minutes after the quake, and most victims were caught while fleeing for higher ground and secure places after surviving the earthquake. This was also the case in [[Aceh]], Indonesia. {{citation needed|date=November 2019}}\n\nWhile there remains the potential for sudden devastation from a tsunami, warning systems can be effective. For example, if there were a very large [[subduction zone]] [[earthquake]] ([[moment magnitude scale|moment magnitude]] 9.0) off the west coast of the [[United States]], people in [[Japan]], would therefore have more than 12 hours (and likely warnings from warning systems in Hawaii and elsewhere) before any tsunami arrived, giving them some time to evacuate areas likely to be affected.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Deep-ocean Assessment and Reporting of Tsunamis|Deep-ocean Assessment and Reporting of Tsunamis (DART)]]\n* [[SOFAR channel|Sound Fixing and Ranging (SOFAR) channel]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Tsunami warning systems}}\n* [http://www.cwarn.org International Tsunami warnings delivered to mobile phones]\n* [http://www.iibc.in/itws A 24/7 mobile SMS Integrated Tsunami Watcher Service]\n* [http://www.tsunami.noaa.gov/warning_system_works.html How does the Tsunami Warning System Work?]\n* [http://ntwc.arh.noaa.gov/ National Tsunami Warning Center]\n* [http://www.tsunami.noaa.gov/warnings_forecasts.html NOAA Tsunami Warnings and Forecasts]\n* [http://espace.library.uq.edu.au/view/UQ:203103 Tsunami Warning Signs on the Enshu Coast of Japan] Shore & Beach, Vol. 78, No. 1, pp.&nbsp;52\u201354, 2010\n* [http://www.bom.gov.au/tsunami/index.shtml Joint Australian Tsunami Warning Centre]\n\n[[Category:Warning systems]]\n[[Category:Tsunami|Warning system]]\n", "text_old": "{{multiple issues|\n{{Editorial|date=April 2011}}\n{{Refimprove|date=April 2011}}\n}}\n\n[[File:Tsunami evac sign Seaside Oregon.JPG|thumb|300px|Evacuation route sign in a low-lying coastal area on the West Coast of the United States]]\nA '''tsunami warning system''' ('''TWS''') is used to detect [[tsunami]]s in advance and issue warnings to prevent loss of life and damage to property. It is made up of two equally important components: a network of sensors to detect tsunamis and a communications infrastructure to issue timely alarms to permit evacuation of the coastal areas.  There are two distinct types of tsunami warning systems: '''international''' and '''regional'''.  When operating, seismic alerts are used to instigate the watches and warnings; then, data from observed sea level height (either shore-based tide gauges or [[Deep-ocean Assessment and Reporting of Tsunamis|DART]] buoys) are used to verify the existence of a tsunami.  Other systems have been proposed to augment the warning procedures; for example, it has been suggested that the duration and frequency content of [[T wave (seismic)|t-wave]] energy (which is earthquake energy trapped in the ocean [[SOFAR channel]]) is indicative of an earthquake's tsunami potential.<ref>Salzberg, 2006</ref>\n\n==History and forecasting==\n{{unreferenced|section|date=June 2017}}\nThe first rudimentary system to alert communities of an impending tsunami was attempted in [[Hawaii]] in the 1920s. More advanced systems were developed in the wake of the April 1, 1946 (caused by the [[1946 Aleutian Islands earthquake]]) and May 23, 1960 (caused by the [[1960 Valdivia earthquake]]) tsunamis which caused massive devastation in [[Hilo, Hawaii]].  While tsunamis travel at between 500 and 1,000&nbsp;km/h (around 0.14 and 0.28&nbsp;km/s) in open water, earthquakes can be detected almost at once as [[seismic wave]]s travel with a typical speed of 4&nbsp;km/s (around 14,400&nbsp;km/h).  This gives time for a possible tsunami forecast to be made and warnings to be issued to threatened areas, if warranted.  Until a reliable model is able to predict which earthquakes will produce significant tsunamis, this approach will produce many more false alarms than verified warnings.\n\n==International  systems (IS)==\n\n===Pacific Ocean===\n[[File:TsunamiHazardSign.svg|right|thumb|Japanese Tsunami warning sign]]\nTsunami warnings ([[Specific Area Message Encoding|SAME]] code:  '''TSW''') for most of the [[Pacific Ocean]] are issued by the [[Pacific Tsunami Warning Center]] (PTWC), operated by the [[United States]] [[NOAA]] in [[Ewa Beach, Hawaii]]. NOAA's [[National Tsunami Warning Center]] (NTWC) in [[Palmer, Alaska]] issues warnings for North America, including Alaska, British Columbia, Oregon, California, the Gulf of Mexico, and the East coast. The PTWC was established in 1949, following the 1946 [[Aleutian Island earthquake]] and a tsunami that resulted in 165 casualties on Hawaii and in Alaska; NTWC was founded in 1967. International coordination is achieved through the International Coordination Group for the Tsunami Warning System in the Pacific, established by the [[Intergovernmental Oceanographic Commission]] of [[UNESCO]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ioc.unesco.org/itsu/ |title=IOC Oceans &#124; United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization |publisher=Ioc.unesco.org |date= |accessdate=2018-10-02}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, The US congressional panel passed a vote to continue funding a global tsunami detection system that gives U.S. officials an accurate forecast in order to decrease damage cause by Tsunamis.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.virginislandsdailynews.com/ap/threatened-by-trump-s-budget-tsunami-warning-system-gets-backing/article_7ab750c2-46dd-57b5-8d51-711f2435e6b5.html|title=Threatened by Trump's budget, tsunami warning system gets backing from congressional panel|last=Times|first=Los Angeles|work=The Virgin Islands Daily News|access-date=2017-07-18|language=en}}</ref>\n\n===Indian Ocean (ICG/IOTWMS)===\n{{main article|Indian Ocean Tsunami Warning System}}\n\n[[File:Tsunami-warning-centre hikkaduwa sri-lanka.jpg|right|thumb|Tsunami Early Warning Tower board in Hikkaduwa, Sri Lanka]]\n\nAfter the [[2004 Indian Ocean earthquake|2004 Indian Ocean Tsunami]] which killed almost 250,000 people, a [[United Nations]] conference was held in January 2005 in [[Kobe]], [[Japan]], and decided that as an initial step towards an [[International Early Warning Programme]], the UN should establish an [[Indian Ocean Tsunami Warning System]]. This resulted in a warning system for Indonesia and other affected areas. Indonesia's system fell out of service in 2012 because the detection buoys were no longer operational. Tsunami prediction is therefore currently limited to detection of seismic activity; there is no system to predict tsunamis based on volcanic eruptions.\n\nIndonesia was hit by tsunamis in [[2018 Sulawesi earthquake and tsunami|September]] and [[2018 Sunda Strait tsunami|December]] 2018. The December 2018 tsunami was caused by a volcano.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2018/12/24/asia/indonesia-tsunami-disaster-year-intl/index.html|title=How Indonesia's tsunami warning system failed its citizens again|last=Griffiths|first=James|date=24 December 2018|work=CNN|access-date=24 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n===North Eastern Atlantic, the Mediterranean and Connected Seas (ICG/NEAMTWS)===\nThe First United Session of the Inter-governmental Coordination Group for the Tsunami Early Warning and Mitigation System in the North Eastern Atlantic, the Mediterranean and connected Seas (ICG/NEAMTWS), established by the [[Intergovernmental Oceanographic Commission]] of [[UNESCO]] Assembly during its 23rd Session in June 2005, through Resolution XXIII.14, took place in [[Rome]] on 21 and 22 November 2005.\n\nThe meeting, hosted by the Government of Italy (the [[Italian Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] and the [[Ministry of the Environment (Italy)|Italian Ministry for the Environment and Protection of Land and Sea]]), was attended by more than 150 participants from 24 countries, 13 organizations and numerous observers.\n\n===Caribbean===\n\nA Caribbean-wide tsunami warning system was planned to be instituted by the year 2010, by representatives of [[Caribbean Community|Caribbean nations]] who met in [[Panama City]] in March 2008. [[Panama]]'s last major tsunami killed 4,500 people in 1882.<ref>[http://uk.reuters.com/article/environmentNews/idUKN1332624020080313 Reuters:Caribbean plans tsunami warning system by 2010]</ref> [[Barbados]] has said it will review or test its tsunami protocol in February 2010 as a regional pilot.<ref>{{cite news\n  |title=Time right to test disaster awareness system |author=\n  |first=Carol |last=Martindale\n  |url=http://www.nationnews.com/news/local/tsunami-protocol-in-full-effect-copy-for-web\n  |newspaper=[[The Daily Nation (Barbados)|Nation Newspaper]]\n  |date=24 January 2010 |page= |pages= |at= |accessdate=24 January 2010\n  |quote=A TSUNAMI PROTOCOL to be tested here next month will help Barbadians be better prepared to deal with natural disasters such as earthquakes. ... Harewood said Barbados was nominated and accepted as the \"pilot state\" for the tsunami protocol which will be discussed from February 22 to 26.  He said the objective of the Standard Operational Procedure and Communications Protocol, which has been being worked on for the last two years, is to provide more information on what must be done in the event of a tsunami, earthquake or any other major disaster.  He noted that one of the things they would be doing was adopting a general public service announcement through the Government Information Service (GIS) to help increase awareness of tsunamis.\n}}</ref>{{update after|2014|7}}\n\n==Regional warning systems==\n[[File:1 Tsunamiwarnsystem in Dili.jpg|thumb|Tsunami warning system in [[East Timor]]]]\n\nRegional (or local) warning system centers use [[seismic]] data about nearby recent earthquakes to determine if there is a possible local threat of a tsunami. Such systems are capable of issuing warnings to the general public (via public address systems and sirens) in less than 15 minutes. Although the [[epicenter]] and [[moment magnitude scale|moment magnitude]] of an underwater quake and the probable tsunami arrival times can be quickly calculated, it is almost always impossible to know whether underwater ground shifts have occurred which will result in tsunami waves. As a result, false alarms can occur with these systems, but the disruption is small, which makes sense due to the highly localized nature of these extremely quick warnings, in combination with how difficult it would be for a false alarm to affect more than a small area of the system. Real tsunamis would affect more than just a small portion.\n{{Citation needed|date=April 2011}}\n\n===Japan===\nJapan has a nationwide tsunami warning system. The system usually issues the warning minutes after an [[Earthquake Early Warning (Japan)|Earthquake Early Warning]] (EEW) is issued, should there be expected waves.<ref>{{cite web|title=Japan Meteorological Agency\uff5cFlow of issuance of information about tsunami and earthquake|url=http://www.data.jma.go.jp/svd/eqev/data/en/guide/info.html|accessdate=15 April 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"2011warning\">{{cite web|title=80 Seconds of Warning for Tokyo|url=https://www.technologyreview.com/s/423274/80-seconds-of-warning-for-tokyo/|website=MIT Technology Review|accessdate=15 April 2016}}</ref> The tsunami warning was issued within 3 minutes with the most serious rating on its warning scale during the [[2011 T\u014dhoku earthquake and tsunami]]; it was rated as a \"major tsunami\", being at least 3&nbsp;m (9.8&nbsp;ft) high.<ref name=\"2011warning\"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Emergency Warning System Starting Shortly|url=http://www.jma.go.jp/jma/en/Emergency_Warning/Leaflet(Emergency_Warning).pdf|accessdate=15 April 2016}}</ref> An improved system was unveiled on March 7, 2013 following the 2011 disaster to better access the waves.<ref>{{cite web|title=Leaflet \"Start of New Tsunami Warning System Operation\"|url=http://www.data.jma.go.jp/svd/eqev/data/en/tsunami/tsunamiwarning-leaflet.pdf|accessdate=15 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Tsunami two years on: Japan finally gets warning system that would have saved hundreds of lives|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/japan/9920042/Tsunami-two-years-on-Japan-finally-gets-warning-system-that-would-have-saved-hundreds-of-lives.html|accessdate=15 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Conveying the warning==\n{{unreferenced|section|date=June 2017}}\n[[File:Okumatsushima tsunami P1130317 rotated.jpg|thumb|Mast with warning system, and sign detailing escape routes, on the coast of [[Okumatsushima]], [[Miyagi Prefecture|Miyagi]] prefecture, [[Japan]] (this coast was severely hit by the [[2011 T\u014dhoku earthquake and tsunami|2011 tsunami]])]]\nDetection and prediction of tsunamis is only half the work of the system. Of equal importance is the ability to warn the populations of the areas that will be affected. All tsunami warning systems feature multiple lines of communications (such as [[Cell Broadcast]], [[SMS]], [[e-mail]], [[fax]], [[radio]], texting and [[teleprinter|telex]], often using hardened dedicated systems) {{citation needed|date=November 2019}} enabling emergency messages to be sent to the [[emergency service]]s and [[armed forces]], as well to population-alerting systems (e.g. [[siren (noisemaker)|sirens]]) and systems like the [[Emergency Alert System]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=UNESCO |url=http://itic.ioc-unesco.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=category&id=1437&Itemid=1437 |website=International Tsunami Information Center |accessdate=5 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Shortcomings==\n{{unreferenced|section|date=June 2017}}\nWith the speed at which tsunami waves travel through open water, no system can protect against a very sudden tsunami, where the coast in question is too close to the [[epicenter]]. A devastating tsunami occurred off the coast of [[Hokkaid\u014d]] in Japan as a result of [[1993 Hokkaid\u014d earthquake|an earthquake on July 12, 1993]]. As a result, 202 people on the small island of [[Okushiri, Hokkaido]] lost their lives, and hundreds more were missing or injured. {{citation needed|date=November 2019}} This tsunami struck just three to five minutes after the quake, and most victims were caught while fleeing for higher ground and secure places after surviving the earthquake. This was also the case in [[Aceh]], Indonesia. {{citation needed|date=November 2019}}\n\nWhile there remains the potential for sudden devastation from a tsunami, warning systems can be effective. For example, if there were a very large [[subduction zone]] [[earthquake]] ([[moment magnitude scale|moment magnitude]] 9.0) off the west coast of the [[United States]], people in [[Japan]], would therefore have more than 12 hours (and likely warnings from warning systems in Hawaii and elsewhere) before any tsunami arrived, giving them some time to evacuate areas likely to be affected.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Deep-ocean Assessment and Reporting of Tsunamis|Deep-ocean Assessment and Reporting of Tsunamis (DART)]]\n* [[SOFAR channel|Sound Fixing and Ranging (SOFAR) channel]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Tsunami warning systems}}\n* [http://www.cwarn.org International Tsunami warnings delivered to mobile phones]\n* [http://www.iibc.in/itws A 24/7 mobile SMS Integrated Tsunami Watcher Service]\n* [http://www.tsunami.noaa.gov/warning_system_works.html How does the Tsunami Warning System Work?]\n* [http://ntwc.arh.noaa.gov/ National Tsunami Warning Center]\n* [http://www.tsunami.noaa.gov/warnings_forecasts.html NOAA Tsunami Warnings and Forecasts]\n* [http://espace.library.uq.edu.au/view/UQ:203103 Tsunami Warning Signs on the Enshu Coast of Japan] Shore & Beach, Vol. 78, No. 1, pp.&nbsp;52\u201354, 2010\n* [http://www.bom.gov.au/tsunami/index.shtml Joint Australian Tsunami Warning Centre]\n\n[[Category:Warning systems]]\n[[Category:Tsunami|Warning system]]\n", "name_user": "172.193.100.170", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(i added more facts.)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tsunami_warning_system"}
{"title_page": "Business consultant", "text_new": "A '''business consultant''' (from [[Latin]] ''consultare'', \"to discuss\") is a [[professional]] who provides professional or [http://brandchanakya.in/ expert advice]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/consultant |title=Consultant &#124; Define Consultant at Dictionary.com |publisher=Dictionary.reference.com |date=2004-03-09 |accessdate=2014-07-20}}</ref> in a particular area such as security ([[information security|electronic]] or [[physical security|physical]]), [[management]], [[accountancy]], [[law]], [[human resources]], [[marketing]] (and [[public relations]]), [[finance]], [[engineering]], [[science]] or any of many other specialized fields.\n\nA consultant is usually an expert or a professional in a specific field and has a wide area of knowledge in a specific subject. Consultants can save their clients time, increase revenue, and maintain resources. <ref>Pieter P. Tordoir (1995). ''The professional knowledge economy: the management and integration services in business organizations.'' p.140.</ref> The role of a consultant outside the medical sphere (where the term is used specifically for a grade of doctor) can fall under one of two general categories:\n* Internal consultant \u2013 someone who operates within an organization but is available to be consulted on areas of specialism by other departments or individuals (acting as clients); or\n* External consultant \u2013 someone who is employed externally (either by a firm or some other agency) whose expertise is provided on a temporary basis, usually for a fee.  As such this type of consultant generally engages with multiple and changing clients.\n\nThe overall impact of a consultant is that clients have access to deeper levels of expertise than would be feasible for them to retain in-house, and may purchase only as much service from the outside consultant as desired. \n\n== References ==\n{{Wiktionary|consultant|consulting}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n<!--==External links==\nPlease do not add consultant agencies or blogs of individual consultants -->\n\n{{Consulting}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Consulting occupations]]\n[[Category:Business occupations]]\n[[Category:Management occupations]]\n", "text_old": "A '''business consultant''' (from [[Latin]] ''consultare'', \"to discuss\") is a [[professional]] who provides professional or expert advice<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/consultant |title=Consultant &#124; Define Consultant at Dictionary.com |publisher=Dictionary.reference.com |date=2004-03-09 |accessdate=2014-07-20}}</ref> in a particular area such as security ([[information security|electronic]] or [[physical security|physical]]), [[management]], [[accountancy]], [[law]], [[human resources]], [[marketing]] (and [[public relations]]), [[finance]], [[engineering]], [[science]] or any of many other specialized fields.\n\nA consultant is usually an expert or a professional in a specific field and has a wide area of knowledge in a specific subject. Consultants can save their clients time, increase revenue, and maintain resources. <ref>Pieter P. Tordoir (1995). ''The professional knowledge economy: the management and integration services in business organizations.'' p.140.</ref> The role of a consultant outside the medical sphere (where the term is used specifically for a grade of doctor) can fall under one of two general categories:\n* Internal consultant \u2013 someone who operates within an organization but is available to be consulted on areas of specialism by other departments or individuals (acting as clients); or\n* External consultant \u2013 someone who is employed externally (either by a firm or some other agency) whose expertise is provided on a temporary basis, usually for a fee.  As such this type of consultant generally engages with multiple and changing clients.\n\nThe overall impact of a consultant is that clients have access to deeper levels of expertise than would be feasible for them to retain in-house, and may purchase only as much service from the outside consultant as desired. \n\n== References ==\n{{Wiktionary|consultant|consulting}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n<!--==External links==\nPlease do not add consultant agencies or blogs of individual consultants -->\n\n{{Consulting}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Consulting occupations]]\n[[Category:Business occupations]]\n[[Category:Management occupations]]\n", "name_user": "Ashishjain3221", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Business_consultant"}
{"title_page": "Zulkifli Hasan", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|name               = Zulkifli Hasan\n|image              = Zulkifli Hasan MPR cropped.jpg\n|imagesize          =\n|caption            = \n|office            = Speaker of [[People's Consultative Assembly]]\n|order              = \n|term_start         = 1 October 2014\n|term_end           = 1 October 2019\n|president          = [[Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono]]<br />[[Joko Widodo]]\n|predecessor        = [[Sidarto Danusubroto]]\n|successor          = [[Bambang Soesatyo]]\n|office2 = [[Partai Amanat Nasional|Leader of Partai Amanat Nasional]]\n|order2 =\n|term_start2 = 1 March 2015\n|term_end2 =\n|predecessor2 = [[Hatta Rajasa]]\n|successor2 =\n|office3           = Minister of Forestry\n|order3              = \n|term_start3         = 22 October 2008\n|term_end3           = 1 October 2014\n|president3          = [[Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono]]\n|predecessor3        = [[Malam Sambat Kaban]]\n|successor3          = [[Chairul Tanjung]] <br /><small> (acting)\n|birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1962|5|17|mf=y}}\n|birth_place        = [[Lampung]], [[Indonesia]]\n|death_date         =\n|death_place        =\n|nationality        = Indonesian\n|party              = [[National Mandate Party]]\n|spouse             = Soraya\n|relations          = Herli Hasan (brother) <br /> Hazizi (brother) <br /> [[Helmi Hasan]] (brother) <br /> Zainudin Hasan (brother)\n|children           = Futri Zulya Savitri <br /> Zita Anjani <br /> M. Farras Nugraha <br /> M. Rafi Haikal\n|alma_mater         = Krisanadwipayana University\n|occupation         = \n|profession         = Politician\n|religion           = [[Sunni Islam]]\n|signature          = \n|website            = http://www.zulhasan.com/\n|footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Zulkifli Hasan''' (born 17 May 1962 in Lampung) is an [[Indonesian people|Indonesian]] politician and has led the Islam-oriented [[National Mandate Party]] (Partai Amanat Nasional, PAN) since 1 March 2015. He was speaker of the [[People's Consultative Assembly|People's Consultative Assembly (MPR)]] from 2014 to 2019. He was Forestry Minister from 22 October 2009 to 1 October 2014.\n\n==Childhood and education==\nZulkifli Hasan was born to Hasan and Siti Zaenab, who were farmers in Pisang village in Penengahan, [[South Lampung Regency|South Lampung]]. In later life, he would claim to have experienced economic hardship as a child, saying he learnt to work hard by selling eggs produced on the farm. He attended a local elementary school from 1969 to 1975. At age 13, his father took him to Tanjungkarang (now called [[Bandar Lampung]]) to enroll him in junior high school level at the State Islamic Teachers Training School (PGAN), against the boy's wishes.<ref>{{cite news|title=Zulkifli Hasan: Man Jadda Wajada!|url=http://rilis.id/Zulkifli-Hasan-Man-Jadda-Wajada|accessdate=1 April 2018|publisher=RILISID|date=13 February 2017}}</ref> While attending PGAN, Zulkifli lived in a rented room in lodgings for boarders. He left PGAN in his fourth year at the school. He took an entrance exam for Madrasah Tsanawiah and passed. Without parental consent, he enrolled at Tandjungkarang State Senior High School. After four months, his father discovered he had switched schools and forced him to leave the high school.\n\nArmed with a little money from his mother, Zul moved to Jakarta. There, he attended State Senior High School 53 and graduated in 1982. In 1986, he enrolled at the Faculty of Economics at Krisnadwipayana University (Unkris) in Jakarta and financed his studies independently. In 2003, he graduated from PPM School of Management.<ref>{{cite news|title=Profil Zulkifli Hasan|url=https://www.viva.co.id/siapa/read/12-zulkifli-hasan|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=PT. Viva Media Baru}}</ref>\n\n== A self-made man ==\nHaving been raised in a farming family, Zulkifli was motivated to seek success beyond a rural environs. In a 2015 interview, he said his parents had wanted him to become like [[Buya Hamka]], an Islam-oriented journalist and author from Sumatra. \"But I refused. I wanted to migrate to Jakarta.\"\n\nArriving in Jakarta as a teenager without prior acquaintances or relatives, Zulkifli supported himself with jobs from washing taxis to selling drinks. He graduated from high school with the highest achievement in his class. He then tried his luck as a door-to-door salesman of pots and later attended college while doing business.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kuwado|first1=Fabian Januarius|title=Zulkifli Hasan Bicara Kesuksesannya sebagai \"Sales\" Panci dan Reformasi PAN|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2015/01/22/21413111/Zulkifli.Hasan.Bicara.Kesuksesannya.sebagai.Sales.Panci.dan.Reformasi.PAN|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Kompas.com|date=22 January 2015}}</ref> After exploring various areas of business, he began working for an ethnic Chinese businessman who sold home furnishings.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kisah Dua Menteri yang Sama-Sama Putra Lampung|url=https://www.jpnn.com/news/kisah-dua-menteri-yang-sama-sama-putra-lampung?page=2|accessdate=9 April 2018|publisher=JPNN.com|date=24 October 2009}}</ref>\n\nIn his later years, Zulkifli once visited Lembaga Pendidikan Insani (LPI), an educational institution whose operational costs came from Islamic donations. He told students there: \"If I ate eggs and could become a minister, then you who eat chicken should be able to become president.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Widjaya|first1=M. Akbar|title=Masa Kecil Menhut Zulkifli Hasan, Makan Sebutir Telur Dibagi Delapan|url=http://www.republika.co.id/berita/nasional/umum/11/10/21/lteug3-masa-kecil-menhut-zulkifli-hasan-makan-sebutir-telur-dibagi-delapan|accessdate=1 April 2018|publisher=Republika.co.id|date=21 October 2011}}</ref>\n\n''Bang'' (Brother) Zul, as he was known, remained close to the people of his hometown in Lampung and would present assistance in times of disaster.\n\n==Business career==\nPrior to becoming a politician, Zulkifli worked as a civil servant and then started his own businesses. His father had advised him not to be a follower but to be a leader, even if that meant starting from something small, so he quit the civil service.<ref>{{cite news|title=Zulkifli Hasan, Keluar dari PNS Jadi Pengusaha Sukses|url=https://finance.detik.com/sosok/d-1943289/zulkifli-hasan-keluar-dari-pns-jadi-pengusaha-sukses|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=detikFinance|date=17 June 2012}}</ref> His older brother, Herli Hasan, says Zulkifli left the civil service because the salary was low.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kisah Dua Menteri yang Sama-Sama Putra Lampung|url=https://www.jpnn.com/news/kisah-dua-menteri-yang-sama-sama-putra-lampung?page=2|accessdate=9 April 2018|publisher=JPNN.com|date=24 October 2009}}</ref>\n\nZulkifli's subsequent corporate positions included:\n\n* President Director of PT Batin Eka Perkasa (1988-2004), then Commissioner (2004-2005). A Jakarta-based company producing kitchen appliances under the Haneda brand-name; now run by Zulkifli's oldest daughter, Futri Zulya Savitri.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mengenal Futri Zulya Savitri, CEO PT Batin Eka Perkasa|url=http://indobisnis.indopos.co.id/read/2016/07/01/11333/Mengenal-Futri-Zulya-Savitri-CEO-PT-Batin-Eka-Perkasa-BEP|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=indopos.co.id|date=1 July 2016}}</ref>\n* President Director of PT Panamas Mitra Inti Lestari (1997-2004). A Bogor-based company selling home appliances and non-stick cookware.<ref>{{cite web|title=Panamas Mitra Inti Lestari PT|url=https://www.daftarperusahaan.com/bisnis/panamas-mitra-inti-lestari-pt|website=Daftarperusahaan.com|publisher=Daftarperusahaan.com|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n* President Director of PT Sarana Bina Insani, Jakarta (2000-2004). A travel bureau.<ref>{{cite news|title=Zul Sudah Diajak Bicara oleh SBY|url=https://issuu.com/tribunlampung/docs/tl1209|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Tribun Lampung|date=12 September 2009}}</ref>\n* Commissioner of PT Hudaya Safari Utama, Jakarta (2000-2006). A haj and umroh travel bureau.\n* Commissioner of [[PT Gudang Garam]], Jakarta (2006-2007).\n\n===Youth entrepreneurship===\nAfter starting his political career, he did not abandon his entrepreneurial interests. He became a motivator for young people and the wider community, particularly in Sumatra, to develop entrepreneurship and create new jobs. He encouraged rural youths to help advance Indonesia's future economic growth. In 2012, he supported a program of the National Mandate Party (PAN) that provided venture capital and training for young entrepreneurs in North Sumatra.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Suryana|first1=Dede|title=Jadi KEK, Sumut Harus Tingkatkan Wirausaha|url=https://economy.okezone.com/read/2012/05/06/320/624714/jadi-kek-sumut-harus-tingkatkan-wirausaha|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Okezone.com|date=6 May 2012}}</ref>\n\n== Early political career ==\nZulkifli was active in the [[Muhammadiyah]] mass Muslim organization, whose members were among the founders of the [[National Mandate Party]] (PAN) in 1998. His first political forays included chairing the Regional Board of Farmers and Fishermen of Lampung Province, serving as deputy chairman of Lampung Sai Community Society, and initiating the Lampung Youth Union in Jakarta. He chaired Muhammadiyah's Institute of Agricultural Laborers and Fishermen for Jakarta from 2000 to 2005. He chaired the Logistics Department of PAN's Central Board from 2000 to 2005.<ref>{{cite news|title=Keberuntungan Zulkifli Hasan menjadi ketua MPR|url=https://www.antaranews.com/berita/457660/keberuntungan-zulkifli-hasan-menjadi-ketua-mpr|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Antara|date=9 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nHe later became deputy chairman of PAN's faction in the House of Representatives, serving as a member of parliament from 2004 to 2009. He was a member of House Commission VI overseeing transportation and infrastructure. In July 2008, he was elected chairman of a special committee that questioned the government's policy to raise fuel prices.<ref>{{cite news|title=Zulkifli Hasan Terpilih Jadi Ketua Pansus Hak Angket BBM|url=https://otomotif.kompas.com/read/2008/07/09/14405974/Zulkifli.Hasan.Terpilih.Jadi.Ketua.Pansus.Hak.Angket.BBM|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Kompas.com|date=9 July 2008}}</ref>\n\nZulkifli was secretary general of PAN's Central Board for 2005 to 2010.<ref>{{cite news|title=Zulkifli Hasan Jadi Sekjen PAN 2005-2010|url=https://nasional.tempo.co/read/59387/zulkifli-hasan-jadi-sekjen-pan-2005-2010|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Tempo.co|date=11 April 2015}}</ref> On 8 October 2011, Zulkifli's oldest daughter Futri Zulya Savitri married PAN founder Amien Rais's third son, Ahmad Mumtaz Rais.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ketika Amien Rais dan Zulkifli Hasan Besanan|url=https://www.jpnn.com/news/ketika-amien-rais-dan-zulkifli-hasan-besanan|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=PT. JPG Multimedia|date=9 October 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Forestry Minister==\n[[File:Zulkifli Hasan.jpg|thumb|right|175px|Zulkifli as forestry minister, in 2013]]\nAfter President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono was re-elected for a second term in 2009, Zulkifli was appointed forestry minister on 21 October 2009. He said his priorities would be the development of production forests (HTI and HTR), reducing forest fires by 20% annually, combating illegal logging, streamlining of overlapping regulations of the central government and regencies for forest sites, and improving forest industry institutions. He also said he would resist temptations and pressure from businessmen and politicians putting themselves before the public interest. \u201cBut temptations are always there everywhere. It\u2019ll pose no problem to us if we just don\u2019t pay attention to them,\u201d he said.<ref>{{cite news|title=Zulkifli Hasan vows to live up to his political contract|url=http://www.pressreader.com/indonesia/the-jakarta-post/20091102/282956741238073|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=2 November 2009}}</ref> Indonesia's Corruption Eradication Commission (KPK) in 2012 declared the Forestry Ministry to be considered the country's most corrupt institution.<ref>{{cite news|title=Indonesia Struggles to Clean Up Corrupt Forestry Sector|url=http://jakartaglobe.id/news/indonesia-struggles-to-clean-up-corrupt-forestry-sector/|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Jakarta Globe|date=1 January 2014}}</ref> To support efforts to eradicate corruption, Zulkifli issued circular No.SE.2 / Menhut-II / 2012 on Gratification Reporting at the Ministry of Forestry. The circular encouraged staff at the ministry to report the gratuities they receive to their superiors to report to first echelon officials and the KPK.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Snowdon|first1=Karon|title=Forestry Ministry Signs an MoU With KPK|url=https://en.tempo.co/read/news/2013/05/21/055482221/Forestry-Ministry-Signs-an-MoU-With-KPK}}</ref> Zulkifli served as forestry minister until 1 October 2014.\n\n===Illegal forest operations===\nIn 2010, the Forestry Ministry promised to crack down on plantation companies operating without permits in Indonesia. In 2011, the ministry admitted hundreds of mining and plantation companies were operating in Central Kalimantan province without correct permits.<ref>{{cite news|title=Activists urge crackdown on 'forest mafia' networks|url=http://www.asia-pacific-solidarity.net/southeastasia/indonesia/netnews/2011/ind05v15.htm#Activists%20urge%20crackdown%20on%20'forest%20mafia'%20networks|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Jakarta Globe|date=3 February 2011}}</ref> Zulkifli said the problem was due to misinterpretations of regional autonomy legislation introduced in 2001. Elfian Effendi of Greenomics Indonesia said it was difficult for the minister to stop the offending companies because they have political links.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Snowdon|first1=Karon|title=Indonesia admits hundreds of companies without forestry permits|url=http://www.radioaustralia.net.au/international/2011-02-02/indonesia-admits-hundreds-of-companies-without-forestry-permits/224918|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=ABC Radio Australia|date=2 February 2011}}</ref> The Forestry Ministry promised to stop issuing new plantation and mine permits in the province and to cooperate with the Corruption Eradication Commission (KPK) to enforce the law.{{Citation needed|date=April 2018}}\n\n===Moratorium on new forest concessions===\nIn January 2011, Zulkifli announced the Forestry Ministry would implement a 2-year moratorium on the issuance of permits for the conversion of primary and peat forests.<ref>{{cite news|title=Govt to implement forest conversion moratorium in January|url=https://en.antaranews.com/news/66951/govt-to-implement-forest-conversion-moratorium-in-january|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Antara|date=13 January 2011}}</ref> Conservationists noted that on the eve of the logging moratorium, the ministry issued 2.9 million hectares of new plantation concessions to 44 firms.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lang|first1=Chris|title=On the eve of the logging moratorium, Indonesia\u2019s Ministry of Forestry issued almost three million hectares of concessions|url=http://www.redd-monitor.org/2011/01/26/on-the-eve-of-the-logging-moratorium-indonesias-ministry-of-forestry-issued-almost-three-million-hectares-of-concessions/|website=REDD-Monitor|publisher=Wordpress|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref> On 20 May 2011, President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono signed a presidential decree putting the two-year moratorium into effect. The decree covered from 64 million to 72 million hectares of primary forest and peatland.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Stolle|first1=Fred|title=Indonesia\u2019s Ambitious Forest Moratorium Moves Forward|url=http://www.wri.org/blog/2011/06/indonesia%E2%80%99s-ambitious-forest-moratorium-moves-forward|website=World Resources Institute|publisher=World Resources Institute|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Allegation of state losses===\nIn May 2013, the Indonesian Forum for Budget Transparency (Fitra) claimed data from the State Audit Agency (BPK) showed the Forestry Ministry had lost or misappropriated Rp 7.1 trillion ($731 million) in 2012. Zulkifli responded by saying the data and description of \u201closses\u201d were inaccurate. He said the actual figure was Rp 6.2 trillion in non-tax revenue the ministry has been unable to collect since 2002. \u201cWe\u2019re continuing to collect on those payments, both at the regional level and at the central level, and to date we\u2019ve whittled down the outstanding amount to just Rp 2.1 trillion,\u201d he said.<ref>{{cite news|title=Indonesian Ministers Deny Claims They Have Lost 8.3t Rupiah|url=http://jakartaglobe.id/news/indonesian-ministers-deny-claims-they-have-lost-8-3t-rupiah/|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Jakarta Globe|date=3 May 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Interview by Harrison Ford===\nOn 9 September 2013, Zulkifli was interviewed by [[Harrison Ford]] for part of a documentary series on climate change and the environment. Presidential adviser Andi Arief complained Ford had attacked the minister with rude questions. He accused Ford and his crew of \u201charassing state institutions\u201d and threatened to deport him.\n\nZulkifli said Ford was emotional because he wanted illegal loggers swiftly arrested at [[Tesso Nilo National Park|Tesso Nilo]] National Park in Sumatra. The minister said Ford did not give him sufficient time to explain the difficulties of catching those who violate forestry laws. He lamented they had not rehearsed the interview before filming commenced.<ref>{{cite news|title=FM bemoans Harrison Ford's attitude|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2013/09/09/fm-bemoans-harrison-ford-s-attitude.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=9 September 2013}}</ref> Ford was making part of a series on climate change called ''[[Years of Living Dangerously]]'' for US television network [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Harrison Ford shocks Indonesian minister with heated climate interview|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2013-09-10/indonesian-minister-shocked-at-harrison-ford-climate-interview/4949316|accessdate=3 April 2018|agency=AFP|publisher=ABC News|date=11 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Hazardous smoke haze===\nDuring Zulkifli's tenure as forestry minister, forests in Sumatra and Kalimantan were burned to clear land for plantations, causing hazardous haze that reached neighboring Singapore and Malaysia. In 2013, Kuntoro Mangkusubroto, the head of Indonesia's presidential working unit for development supervision and control, said many fires were on land owned by Asia Pulp and Paper (APP) and Asia Pacific Resources International Limited. Zulkifli said there was no strong evidence against the two companies.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lim|first1=Leonard|title=MFA seeks answers from Jakarta to conflicting views on whether Singapore firms caused haze|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/mfa-seeks-answers-from-jakarta-to-conflicting-views-on-whether-singapore-firms-caused-haze|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=The Straits Times|date=25 June 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2013, Zulkifli blamed the severity of the haze on a five-year weather cycle. \"Every five years, the weather becomes extremely dry. The wind is also much stronger and moves in a circular motion. So, when there is burning, fire spreads very quickly... Due to the dry season, it takes time for firefighters to locate the water sources. By the time water is irrigated to the hot spots, the fire would have spread.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lim|first1=Joyce|title=Severity of haze 'due to 5-year cycle' of dry weather|url=http://www.asiaone.com/health/severity-haze-due-5-year-cycle-dry-weather|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=The Straits Times|date=28 June 2013}}</ref> Responding to allegations that plantation and forestry companies were responsible for the fires, Zulkifli was quoted by [[Tempo Magazine (Indonesia)|''Tempo'' magazine]] as saying the companies must be defended because they pay taxes.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cahyadi|first1=Firdaus|title=When People's Safety are Sacrificed to Defend Companies|url=https://en.tempo.co/read/news/2013/07/07/080494143/When-Peoples-Safety-are-Sacrificed-to-Defend-Companies|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Tempo.co|date=7 July 2013}}</ref> He said 14 people had been arrested on suspicion of starting fires, 11 of them linked to companies and three of them smallholders. \"If proven guilty they could be jailed for five years and have their permits revoked,\" he said.<ref>{{cite news|title=Indonesia allocates Rp100 billion to overcome forest fires|url=https://en.antaranews.com/news/89602/indonesia-allocates-rp100-billion-to-overcome-forest-fires|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Antara|date=28 June 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2014, Zulkifli supported calls by the National Police and Indonesian Military for the shooting of people found burning forests if they resist arrest. He acknowledged the people responsible for forest fires were seeking to open up new land for oil palm plantations.<ref>{{cite news|title=Forestry Minister Echoes Calls for Strict Action on Haze Issue|url=http://jakartaglobe.id/news/forestry-minister-echoes-calls-strict-action-haze-issue/|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Jakarta Globe|date=18 March 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, anti-haze activist Syahrul Fitra accused Zulkifli of allowing corporations to burn forests and causing the haze crisis. He claimed Zulkifli had allegedly given permission for the burning of over 1.3 million hectares of forests be used for plantations. He said law enforcers should arrest any officials responsible for the haze and called for an investigation into possible corruption in the issuance of permits. Zulkifli denied any wrongdoing.<ref>{{cite news|title=Former Indonesian Forestry Minister blamed by activist for haze crisis|url=http://www.todayonline.com/world/asia/former-indonesian-forestry-minister-blamed-activist-haze-crisis|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Mediacorp Press Ltd|date=1 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Riau forestry corruption case===\nIn August 2014, Zulkifli visited [[Riau]] province and encouraged proposals to change the status of forest land owned by locals so it could become part of 1,638,249 hectares allowed by the [[Indonesian Ministry of Forestry|Forestry Ministry]] for conversion into non-forest land.\n\nRiau governor Annas Ma'mun's administration responded by sending a proposal to Zulkifli, who gave his approval to some of the areas. Annas later revised the proposal, adding some land owned by palm-oil businessman Gulat Manurung, who paid a bribe of S$156,000 and Rp 500 million. Annas later stated Zulkifli had approved and issued the conversion permit.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Budiari|first1=Indra|title=MPR speaker faces more questions from KPK|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2014/11/13/mpr-speaker-faces-more-questions-kpk.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=13 November 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 November 2014, Zulkifli was questioned as a witness by the [[Corruption Eradication Commission]] (KPK) in the case against Annas. Zulkifli denied approving the permit. Annas said he had been on his way to meet with Zulkifli when he was arrested by the KPK in a sting operation in September 2014.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Budiari|first1=Indra|title=Governor piles more allegations on Zulkifli|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2014/11/19/governor-piles-more-allegations-zulkifli.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=19 November 2014}}</ref>\n\nTestifying at Annas's corruption trial in April 2015, Zulkifli admitted he had met with the director of PT Duta Palma, Surya Darmadi, to discuss a forest clearing permit. Surya was linked to the case by Gulat, who said he helped PT Duta Palma to meet with Annas to enable the company to convert 18,000 hectares of land.<ref>{{cite news|last1=S.|first1=Iqbal T. Lazuardi|title=Zulkifli Hasan Admits Meeting Company CEO|publisher=Tempo.co|date=8 April 2015}}</ref> Gulat was in February 2015 sentenced to three years in jail.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Movanita|first1=Ambaranie Nadia Kemala|title=Suap Gubernur Riau Rp 2 Miliar, Gulat Manurung Divonis Tiga Tahun Penjara|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2015/06/25/court-sentences-riau-governor-6-years-prison-corrupt.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Kompas.com|date=23 February 2015}}</ref> Annas was in June 2015 sentenced to six years in jail.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dipa|first1=Arya|title=Court sentences Riau governor to 6 years in prison for corrupt|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2015/06/25/court-sentences-riau-governor-6-years-prison-corrupt.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jajkarta Post|date=25 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Bogor land conversion case===\nZulkifli was questioned by the KPK on 11 November 2014 over the illegal issuance of a land conversion permit for a luxury housing project in [[Bogor Regency|Bogor]], [[West Java]]. The project was developed by property firm [[Sentul City, Indonesia|PT Sentul City]]. Former Bogor regent Rachmat Yasin received Rp 4.5 billion in bribes from Sentul City president director Kwee Cahyadi Kumala, who is president commissioner of property company PT Bukit Jonggol Asri (BJA), the main shareholder of Sentul City. KPK in December 2014 raided the Forestry Ministry to seize evidence. Zulkifli denied any wrongdoing. The Forestry Ministry's director general for planning, Bambang Supijanto, said Zulkifli had rejected BJA's proposal to convert nearly 3,000 acres of forest area for housing projects in Bogor because it lacked some requirements.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Halim|first1=Haeril|title=KPK raids ministry's office in land-conversion case|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2014/12/17/kpk-raids-ministry-s-office-land-conversion-case.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=17 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Forest smallholdings and education===\nZulkifli sought to improve the performance and image of the Forestry Ministry through two programs: one targeting the growth of agriculture through smallholdings in forest areas, and the other promoting environmental education. The first was the simplification of the application procedure for the development of smallholdings under the Community Nursery (''Kebun Bibit Rakyat'', KBR) scheme, introduced in 2010 and simplified in 2011.<ref>{{cite news |title=Prosedur Kebun Bibit Rakyat Dipermudah |url=https://ekonomi.kompas.com/read/2011/03/16/0352377/prosedur.kebun.bibit.rakyat.dipermudah |accessdate=6 August 2018 |publisher=Kompas Cyber Media |date=16 March 2011}}</ref> The second is the Forest Education program, which involves students visiting selected forest areas and planting trees.{{Citation needed|date=August 2018}}\n\n===Flurry of decrees===\nConservation groups have alleged that after Joko Widodo had won Indonesia\u2019s presidential election in July 2014, Zulkifli realized he would not retain his cabinet position because PAN was not part of the incoming ruling coalition, so he therefore started issuing more ministerial decrees, right up to his final week in office, when 100 decrees were signed. Many of the decrees granted new concessions for timber and logging companies, or allowed forest land to be used by oil palm plantation companies. Much of the land in question is in Papua province.<ref>{{cite web|title=September 29th 2014, a terrible day for Papua\u2019s forests|url=https://awasmifee.potager.org/?p=1600|website=awasMIFEE!|publisher=awasMIFEE!|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref> Greenomics Indonesia said Zulkfli, during his tenure as minister, granted permits for 1.64 million acres of forest land to be used for farming, including for oil palm plantations.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hendartyo|first1=Muhammad|title=Greenomics says PAN Cadre Granted More Land Permits Than Jokowi|url=https://en.tempo.co/read/news/2018/03/22/055916893/Greenomics-says-PAN-Cadre-Granted-More-Land-Permits-Than-Jokowi|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Tempo.co|date=22 March 2018}}</ref> Zulkifli in March 2018 defended his action, saying Papua needed more land for sugar cultivation.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Novaria|first1=Astri|title=Respon Zulkifli Hasan Jawab Tudingan Greenomics|url=http://mediaindonesia.com/read/detail/151069-respon-zulkifli-hasan-jawab-tudingan-greenomics|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Media Indonesia|date=23 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==MPR Speaker==\n[[File:Ali Larijani meeting with Indonesian parliament chairman Zulkifli Hasan 02.jpg|thumb|right|175px|Zulkifli in parliament, December 2016]]\nOn 8 October 2014, Zulkifli was sworn in as speaker of the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) for the 2014-2019 period. His appointment was supported by [[Prabowo Subianto]]'s Red-and-White Coalition following Prabowo's loss of the [[2014 Indonesian presidential election|2014 presidential election]] to [[Joko Widodo|Joko \"Jokowi\" Widodo]]. Although PAN was then a member of the opposition coalition, Zulkifli promised to uphold the interests of all Indonesians and not just those of his political supporters. Jokowi's coalition had wanted [[Oesman Sapta Odang]] as MPR speaker, but Zulkifli defeated Oesman by 347 to 330 votes.<ref>{{cite news|title=Zulkifli Hasan inaugurated as new speaker of People's Consultative Assembly|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2014/10/08/zulkifli-hasan-inaugurated-new-speaker-people-s-consultative-assembly.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=8 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nOne of Zulkifli's first tasks as MPR speaker was to lead the inauguration ceremony of Indonesia's seventh president, Joko Widodo, on 20 October 2014. He was credited for ensuring the event was attended by the losing presidential candidate Prabowo Subianto, who had vigorously rejected the election result.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hariyadi|first1=Yoseph|title=Jokowi inaugurated as Indonesia's new president|url=https://en.antaranews.com/news/96163/jokowi-inaugurated-as-indonesias-new-president|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=20 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 December 2014, Zulkifli said protests against then-Jakarta governor [[Basuki Tjahaja Purnama]], better known as Ahok, on the basis of his religion and race were unacceptable. Ahok, a Christian of Chinese ethnicity, faced opposition from conservative Muslim groups. \"I strongly protest those who protest against Ahok because he's ethnic Chinese or because of his religion. If you want to criticize, go ahead, but do not make it about ethnicity, religion or race, as we are united in diversity,\" he said.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ketua MPR: Tak Boleh Ada yang Protes Ahok Karena Etnis dan Agamanya|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-2784784/ketua-mpr-tak-boleh-ada-yang-protes-ahok-karena-etnis-dan-agamanya|accessdate=5 April 2018|publisher=detikcom|date=22 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Stance on alcohol and drugs===\nIn May 2016, Zulkifli called for tighter regulations on the sale of alcohol, saying it has negative social consequences, including death and crimes of obscenity.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Zulfikar|first1=Muhammad|title=Zulkifli Hasan: Peredaran Miras di Indonesia Harus Diatur|url=http://www.tribunnews.com/mpr-ri/2016/05/27/zulkifli-hasan-peredaran-miras-di-indonesia-harus-diatur|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Tribunnews.com|date=27 May 2016}}</ref> Indonesia already bans the sale of alcohol to minors.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wahyuningsih|first1=Merry|title=Tak Boleh Minum Bir Sebelum Umur 21 Tahun|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/gaya-hidup/20141031121011-255-9076/tak-boleh-minum-bir-sebelum-umur-21-tahun|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=CNN Indonesia|date=31 October 2014}}</ref> In January 2018, Zulkifli claimed eight parties in the national parliament were in favor of open alcohol sales at small shops. He said alcoholic drinks should be rejected firmly.<ref>{{cite news|title=Delapan Fraksi Setujui Penjualan Miras Secara Bebas|url=https://www.jawapos.com/read/2018/01/20/182792/delapan-fraksi-setujui-penjualan-miras-secara-bebas|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=PT Jawa Pos Grup Multimedia|date=20 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2016, Zulkifli called for smoking to be banned as it contributes to \"ignorance and poverty\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Aco|first1=Hasanudin|title=Zulkifli Hasan: Stop Merokok!|url=http://www.tribunnews.com/nasional/2016/02/16/zulkifli-hasan-stop-merokok|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=TRIBUNnews.com|date=February 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2018, Zulkifli said drug traffickers should be shot dead, while drug users should be rehabilitated rather than imprisoned, as most of Indonesia's prison inmates are drug offenders.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tegas!! Zulkifli Hasan Sebut Bandar Narkoba Ditembak Mati|url=http://www.inikata.com/tegas-zulkifli-hasan-sebut-bandar-narkoba-ditembak-mati/|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=PT. Indo Network Intermedia|date=12 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Opposition to LGBT===\nIn March 2016, Zulkifli said the lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender (LGBT) movement should have no place in Indonesia, but he warned against violence and discrimination. \"As a movement, the existence of LGBT must be opposed. We must limit its room to move. However, as individual people, they must be protected like any other citizen,\" he said.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Nurbinato|first1=Bambang|title=More political leaders speak out against LGBT|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2016/03/04/more-political-leaders-speak-out-against-lgbt.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=21 March 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2018, Zulkifli falsely claimed five parties in the House of Representatives were supporting a bill to legalize same-sex marriage. His statement was refuted by House speaker [[Bambang Soesatyo]],<ref>{{cite news|last1=La Batu|first1=Safrin|title=MPR speaker\u2019s remarks on LGBT spark controversy|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2018/01/23/mpr-speaker-s-remarks-lgbt-spark-controversy.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=23 January 2018}}</ref> and prompted other major parties to affirm their opposition to gay rights.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Knight|first1=Kyle|title=Why criminalizing LGBT relationships is misguided|url=http://www.atimes.com/criminalising-lgbt-relations-indonesia-preposterous/|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Asia Times|date=14 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Protecting LGBTs|url=https://en.tempo.co/read/news/2018/02/06/314915509/Protecting-LGBTs|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Tempo.co|date=6 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Chairman of PAN==\nPAN held a congress in Bali over 28 February to 2 March 2015 to choose a chairman for the 2015-2020 period. Among those considered contenders were Zulkifli, then-incumbent chairman Hatta Rajasa and deputy chairman Dradjad Wibowo.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tiga Nama Calon Ketua Umum PAN|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2014/12/18/09333521/Tiga.Nama.Calon.Ketua.Umum.PAN|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Komps.com|date=18 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nZulkifli announced his candidacy on 19 January 2015 in Surabaya. The Chairman of PAN's Youth Front Advisory Council, Hanafi Rais, said Zulkfli wanted the party to focus on defending the interests of the people, as well as giving local party officials full authority in determining regional leadership boards, and improving the performances of regional heads.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Stefanie|first1=Christie|title=Deklarasi Ketua Umum PAN, Zulkifli Hasan Bawa 4 Gagasan|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20150121121055-32-26195/deklarasi-ketua-umum-pan-zulkifli-hasan-bawa-4-gagasan|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=CNN Indonesia|date=21 January 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 March 2015, Zulkifli was narrowly elected PAN chairman, receiving 292 votes, while Hatta Rajasa received 286 votes.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Aritonang|first1=Margareth S.|title=MPR speaker elected new PAN chief|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2015/03/02/mpr-speaker-elected-new-pan-chief.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=2 March 2015}}</ref> After his election, Zulkifli insisted PAN would remain part of Prabowo Subianto's opposition coalition.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sihaloho|first1=Markus Junianto|title=PAN Will Remain in Opposition, New Chairman Zulkifli Says|url=http://jakartaglobe.id/news/pan-will-remain-opposition-new-chairman-zulkifli-says/|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Jakarta Globe|date=2 March 2015}}</ref> On 2 September 2015, Zulkifli announced PAN was switching its allegiance to Jokowi's ruling coalition in order to help the government's programs succeed.<ref>{{cite news|title=PAN Officially Switches Sides, Joins Jokowi's Coalition|url=http://jakartaglobe.id/news/pan-officially-switches-sides-joins-jokowis-coalition/|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Jakarta Globe|date=2 September 2015}}</ref> On 9 August 2018, Zulkifli shifted PAN's allegiance back to Prabowo amid allegations that Prabowo's running mate for the 2019 presidential election, Sandiaga Uno, had paid Rp 500 billion to PAN in order to secure his nomination. PAN denied the allegation.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Saputro |first1=Febrianto Adi |title=PAN actually wants Anies Baswedan to run with Prabowo |url=https://www.republika.co.id/berita/en/national-politics/18/08/23/pdxafc414-pan-actually-wants-anies-baswedan-to-run-with-prabowo |accessdate=25 August 2018 |publisher=Republika.co.id |date=24 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=PAN, PKS deny getting Rp 500b to let Sandiaga become VP candidate |url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2018/08/09/pan-pks-deny-getting-rp-500b-to-let-sandiaga-become-vp-candidate.html |accessdate=25 August 2018 |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=9 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Money politics===\nIn February 2017, Zulkifli urged Indonesians to avoid all forms of money politics in regional elections. \u201cThe sovereignty and power are fully in the hands of the people. Do not trade it for money or staple foods,\u201d he said.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sihaloho|first1=Markus Junianto|title=MPR Speaker Zulkifli Hasan Calls on Public to Avoid Money Politics in Regional Elections|url=http://jakartaglobe.id/news/mpr-speaker-zulkifli-hasan-calls-on-public-to-avoid-money-politics-in-regional-elections/|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Jakarta Globe|date=14 February 2017}}</ref> On 6 March 2018, Zulkifli was filmed giving money to women in a public transport vehicle at a market in [[Muara Enim Regency|Muara Enim]] in [[South Sumatra]] province, ahead of the election for the regent of Muara Enim. He was accompanied at the market by regency head candidate Syamsul Bahri, who is supported by PAN.<ref>{{cite news|title=Adriansyah Laporkan Balik Cabub Syamsul Bahri Ke Polres Muara Enim|url=http://www.palugadanews.com/2018/03/adriansyah-laporkan-balik-cabub-syamsul-bahri-ke-polres-muara-enim/|accessdate=7 April 2018|publisher=Palugadanews.com|date=5 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Inge|first1=Nefri|title=PAN Bantah Zulkifli Hasan Lakukan Politik Uang di Pilkada Muara Enim|url=http://www.liputan6.com/pilkada/read/3373367/pan-bantah-zulkifli-hasan-lakukan-politik-uang-di-pilkada-muara-enim|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Liputan6.com|date=14 March 2018}}</ref> The Election Supervisory Agency (Panwaslu) of Muara Enim conducted an investigation and attempted to summon Zulkifli for questioning but he was too busy to attend.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Inge|first1=Nefri|title=Terekam Bagi-Bagi Duit, Zulkifli Hasan Akan Diperiksa Panwas Muara Enim|url=http://www.liputan6.com/pilkada/read/3370498/terekam-bagi-bagi-duit-zulkifli-hasan-akan-diperiksa-panwas-muara-enim|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Liputan6.com|date=14 March 2018}}</ref> PAN officials denied the handing out of money in the presence of the candidate constituted money politics, arguing Syamsul Bahri's presence was his own initiative.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Inge|first1=Nefri|title=PAN Bantah Zulkifli Hasan Lakukan Politik Uang di Pilkada Muara Enim|url=http://www.liputan6.com/pilkada/read/3373367/pan-bantah-zulkifli-hasan-lakukan-politik-uang-di-pilkada-muara-enim|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Liputan6.com|date=14 March 2018}}</ref> Panwaslu later concluded Zulkifli had not been trying to influence voters to choose a particular candidate.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Inge|first1=Nefri|title=Alasan Panwas Muara Enim Bebaskan Zulkifli Hasan|url=http://www.liputan6.com/pilkada/read/3382311/alasan-panwas-muara-enim-bebaskan-zulkifli-hasan|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Liputan6.com|date=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Presidential ambition===\nIn February 2018, Zulkifli said he would be ready to contest Indonesia's [[2019 Indonesian presidential election|2019 presidential election]] if he is nominated.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Triansyah|first1=Isra|title=Zulkifli Hasan Siap Maju Capres jika Diusung PAN|url=https://nasional.sindonews.com/read/1283700/12/zulkifli-hasan-siap-maju-capres-jika-diusung-pan-1519128456|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=SINDOnews.com|date=20 February 2018}}</ref> He later acknowledged any presidential nominee would likely require the backing of a coalition of parties.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Purbaya|first1=Angling Adhitya|title=Zulkifli Perhitungkan Syarat Kursi 20% Untuk Ikut Pilpres|url=https://news.detik.com/berita-jawa-tengah/d-3943561/zulkifli-perhitungkan-syarat-kursi-20-untuk-ikut-pilpres|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=detikcom|date=29 March 2018}}</ref> In April 2018, he said he would be PAN's presidential candidate, despite speculation the party might choose former military commander [[Gatot Nurmantyo]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bayhaqi|first1=Ahda|title=Zulkifli Hasan sebut PAN tak akan usung Gatot di Pilpres 2019|url=https://www.merdeka.com/politik/zulkifli-hasan-sebut-pan-tak-akan-usung-gatot-di-pilpres-2019.html|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Merdeka.com|date=4 April 2018}}</ref> PAN ended up supporting Prabowo Subianto for the 2019 presidential election.<ref>{{cite news |title=Zulkifli Hasan Reveals Prabowo-Sandiaga Campaign Team |url=https://en.tempo.co/read/news/2018/08/18/055920916/Zulkifli-Hasan-Reveals-Prabowo-Sandiaga-Campaign-Team |accessdate=25 August 2018 |publisher=Tempo.co |date=18 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2020 chair fight===\nOn 11 February 2020, Zulkifli was re-elected as PAN leader for another five-year period at a congress marred by violence.<ref>{{cite news |title=Zulkifli Reelected PAN Chairman in Chaotic Congress |url=https://jakartaglobe.id/news/zulkifli-reelected-pan-chairman-in-chaotic-congress |accessdate=14 February 2020 |publisher=Jakarta Globe |date=12 February 2020}}</ref> At least 10 people were injured when supporters of Zulkifli and his challenger Mulfachri Harahap threw chairs at each other.<ref>{{cite news |title=At least 10 injured in violent dispute during second day of PAN congress |url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/02/12/at-least-10-injured-in-violent-dispute-during-second-day-of-pan-congress.html |accessdate=14 February 2020 |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=12 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life and family==\nZulkifli is married to Soraya and they have four children: Futri Zulya Savitri, Zita Anjani, Farras Nugraha and Rafi Haikal.\n\nOldest daughter Futri Zulya Savitri studied in Australia, married a son of Amien Rais and runs a family business making household and kitchen appliances.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Suryadi|first1=Dede|title=Liku-liku Futri Membenahi Haneda|url=https://swa.co.id/swa/profile/profile-entrepreneur/liku-liku-futri-membenahi-haneda|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=SWA Online Magazine|date=11 February 2017}}</ref>\n\nOldest son, Farras Nugraha, studied in the UK and is now a businessman. In September 2017, Farras married Milka Anisya Norosiya. Among their wedding guests were military commander General [[Gatot Nurmantyo]] and senior politicians Oesman Sapta Odang, Amien Rais, [[Hidayat Nur Wahid]], [[Aburizal Bakrie]] and [[Akbar Tandjung]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Laksana|first1=Bisma  Alief|title=Panglima TNI Hingga Ketua DPD Jadi Saksi Nikah Putra Zulkifli Hasan|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/3655732/panglima-tni-hingga-ketua-dpd-jadi-saksi-nikah-putra-zulkifli-hasan|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=detikcom|date=24 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nZulkifli's second daughter, Zita Anjani, studied in London and in 2015 opened an early learning school called Kids Republic. His youngest child, Rafi Haikal, chose to study architecture in New York.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Septianto|first1=Bayu|title=Dari Kursi Bisnis ke MPR, Zulkifli Hasan Ingin Bangun Sekolah di Masa Tua|url=https://news.okezone.com/read/2018/01/20/337/1847853/dari-kursi-bisnis-ke-mpr-zulkifli-hasan-ingin-bangun-sekolah-di-masa-tua|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Okezone News|date=20 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Brothers===\nZulkifli has four brothers, including three who also became politicians: Zainudin Hasan (born 1965),  Hazizi (1976) and [[Helmi Hasan]] (1979). The oldest brother in the family is Herli Hasan.\n\nHelmi Hasan, who became mayor of Bengkulu in 2013, viewed Zulkifli not only as an older brother but also as a parent to be obeyed and respected.<ref>{{cite news|title=Dibalik \"Insya Allah\" Helmi Hasan|url=http://bengkuluekspress.com/dibalik-insya-allah-helmi-hasan/|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Bengkuluekspress.com|date=21 January 2013}}</ref> Zulkifli, Helmi and Zainudin founded Insan Cendikia Kalianda Lampung Indonesia Foundation, which built a free school for children from poor families in Lampung.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Supriyadi|first1=Eko|title=Zulkifli Hasan Tinjau SMA Kebangsaan di Lampung|url=http://www.republika.co.id/berita/mpr-ri/berita-mpr/16/03/17/o46sy3254-zulkifli-hasan-tinjau-sma-kebangsaan-di-lampung|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=republika.co.id|date=17 March 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2015, Helmi Hasan was declared a suspect by Bengkulu Attorney General's Office for allegedly embezzling Rp 11.4 billion ($870,000) of social aid from the city's 2012-2013 budget.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bengkulu Mayor Named Corruption Suspect|url=http://jakartaglobe.id/news/bengkulu-mayor-named-corruption-suspect/|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Jakarta Globe|date=18 March 2015}}</ref> Helmi filed a pre-trial motion, which was accepted on 9 September 2015 by Bengkulu City State Court, so he did not stand trial.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Supriatin|title=Pengadilan batalkan status tersangka wali kota Bengkulu Helmi Hasan|url=https://www.merdeka.com/peristiwa/pn-bengkulu-batalkan-status-tersangka-wali-kota-bengkulu-helmi-hasan.html|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Merdeka.com|date=10 September 2015}}</ref> The former head of Bengkulu City's Office for Management of Regional Revenue, Finance and Assets, M. Sofyan, in September 2017 testified Bengkulu Regional Secretary, Marjon, had ordered him to release Rp 500 million in state funds to pay for the success of Helmi's pre-trial motion.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rahmadani|first1=Yetti|title=Terkuak, Rp 500 Juta Selamatkan Helmi Hasan Dari Praperadilan Bansos|url=http://www.rmolbengkulu.com/read/2017/09/06/4705/Terkuak,-Rp-500-Juta-Selamatkan-Helmi-Hasan-Dari-Praperadilan-Bansos-|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Rakyat Merdeka Online|date=6 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2015, Zainudin Hasan was elected regent of South Lampung regency for the 2016-2021 period.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mualifah|first1=Siti|title=Zainuddin-Nanang Menangi Pilkada Lampung Selatan Versi KPU|url=http://www.jejamo.com/zainuddin-nanang-menangi-pilkada-lampung-selatan-versi-kpu.html|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=jejamo.com|date=16 December 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2017, police in Bandar Lampung city named a Hazizi a fraud suspect for allegedly asking a contractor to pay a bribe of Rp 515 million in order to obtain a contract for infrastructure projects worth Rp 3.5 billion in South Lampung regency, where his brother Zainudin is regent.<ref>{{cite news|title=Pernah Tersangka Penipuan Proyek Hazizi mundur dari dewan|url=https://be1lampung.com/propinsi/pernah-tersangka-penipuan-proyek|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=PT Besatu Lampung Media|date=14 May 2017}}</ref> The contractor, Syahruddin, died in May 2016 without ever receiving the allegedly promised contract. His eldest son later reported Hazizi to police.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rinando|first1=Romi|title=Hazizi, Adik Ketua MPR Zulkifli Hasan Ditetapkan Tersangka Kasus Dugaan Penipuan Proyek|url=http://lampung.tribunnews.com/2017/02/10/hazizi-adik-ketua-mpr-zulkifli-hasan-ditetapkan-tersangka-kasus-dugaan-penipuan-proyek|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Tribun Lampung|date=10 February 2017}}</ref> In May 2017, Hazizi resigned from his seat in Lampung legislative assembly \"for no specific reason\" apart from \"wanting to concentrate on worship\", according to one of his colleagues in PAN.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Yulianto|first1=Beni|title=Adik Kandung Ketua MPR Mengundurkan Diri dari DPRD Lampung|url=http://lampung.tribunnews.com/2017/05/09/adik-kandung-ketua-mpr-mengundurkan-diri-dari-dprd-lampung|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Tribun Lampung|date=9 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Martial arts===\nZulkifli is a practitioner of [[kyokushin]], a type of full contact karate. He served as chairman of the Board of Supervisors of Kyokushinkan International Indonesia. In June 2010, he received an honorary black belt from the supreme leader of Kyokushin International.<ref>{{cite web|title=Honorary Black-Belt submission to H. Zulkifli Hasan SE. MM.|url=http://www.kyokushinkan-indonesia.org/eng/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=36&Itemid=38|website=Kyokushinkan Indonesia|publisher=Kyokushinkan Indonesia|accessdate=9 April 2018}}</ref> Zulkifli is also a practitioner of [[Tarung Derajat]], a full body contact Indonesian mixed martial art. He was chairman of the Tarung Derajat Sports Family from 2010-2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tarung Derajat Tampil di SEA Games 2011|url=https://sport.tempo.co/read/252294/tarung-derajat-tampil-di-sea-games-2011|accessdate=9 April 2018|agency=Tempo.co|date=2 June 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Honors==\nOn 26 July 2007, Jakarta's PPM School of Management presented Zulkifli with the Kadarman Award, which is given to successful alumni.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sekjen DPP PAN Zulkifli Hasan Terima Kadarman Award|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/809996/sekjen-dpp-pan-zulkifli-hasan-terima-kadarman-award?nd771104bcj=|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=detikcom|date=26 July 2007}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 July 2010, Zulkifli received a nobility title from Solo Palace in Central Java. He was bestowed the title of Kanjeng Pangeran (Prince) Noto Wononagoro for his efforts to preserve Javanese culture.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Amri |first1=Arfi Bambani |title=Jupe dan Zulkifli Hasan Dapat Gelar Bangsawan |url=https://www.viva.co.id/berita/nasional/163297-jupe-dan-zulkifli-hasan-dapat-gelar-bangsawan |accessdate=6 August 2018 |publisher=PT Viva Media Baru |date=8 July 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2014, President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono presented Zulkifli with the Bintang Jasa Mahaputra Adipradana medal for his services to the country.<ref>{{cite web|title=Menhut Menerima Bintang Jasa Mahaputra Adipradana|url=http://www.forda-mof.org/index.php/berita/post/1795|website=Ministry of Environment and Forestry Republic of Indonesia|publisher=Badan litbang & Inovasi Kementerian Lingkungan Hidup & Kehutanan|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 November 2017, Zulkifli was awarded the title of Pangeran Kerta Jaya Alam Nata from an organization of residents of [[Lubuklinggau]] in  South Sumatra. The title, which means the leader of the people who carries out the mandate, was presented to him for \"consistently defending the people\". Organizers said Zulkifli is the only person to receive the title.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tambak |first1=Ruslan |title=Zulkifli Hasan Satu-satunya Yang Diberi Gelar Pangeran Kerta Jaya Alam Nata |url=https://www.rmol.co/read/2017/11/15/314583/Zulkifli-Hasan-Satu-satunya-Yang-Diberi-Gelar-Pangeran-Kerta-Jaya-Alam-Nata- |accessdate=6 August 2018 |publisher=Rakyat Merdeka Online |date=15 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Ministry of Forestry (Indonesia)|Ministry of Forestry of the Republic of Indonesia]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://zulkiflihasan.info/ Official website]\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{succession box| title=[[Forestry minister]] of [[Indonesia]] | before=[[Malam Sambat Kaban]] | after=[[Chairul Tanjung]]| years=2009\u20132014}} \n{{s-bef|before=[[Sidarto Danusubroto]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Speaker of the People's Consultative Assembly|years=2014\u20132019}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Bambang Soesatyo]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Leaders of Indonesian political parties}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hasan, Zulk}}\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Lampung]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of Indonesia]]\n[[Category:National Mandate Party politicians]]\n[[Category:Opposition to same-sex marriage]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|name               = Zulkifli Hasan\n|image              = Zulkifli Hasan MPR cropped.jpg\n|imagesize          =\n|caption            = \n|office            = Speaker of [[People's Consultative Assembly]]\n|order              = \n|term_start         = 1 October 2014\n|term_end           = 1 October 2019\n|president          = [[Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono]]<br />[[Joko Widodo]]\n|predecessor        = [[Sidarto Danusubroto]]\n|successor          = [[Bambang Soesatyo]]\n|office2 = [[Partai Amanat Nasional|Leader of Partai Amanat Nasional]]\n|order2 =\n|term_start2 = 1 March 2015\n|term_end2 =\n|predecessor2 = [[Hatta Rajasa]]\n|successor2 =\n|office3           = Minister of Forestry\n|order3              = \n|term_start3         = 22 October 2008\n|term_end3           = 1 October 2014\n|president3          = [[Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono]]\n|predecessor3        = [[Malam Sambat Kaban]]\n|successor3          = [[Chairul Tanjung]] <br /><small> (acting)\n|birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1962|5|17|mf=y}}\n|birth_place        = [[Lampung]], [[Indonesia]]\n|death_date         =\n|death_place        =\n|nationality        = Indonesian\n|party              = [[National Mandate Party]]\n|spouse             = Soraya\n|relations          = Herli Hasan (brother) <br /> Hazizi (brother) <br /> [[Helmi Hasan]] (brother) <br /> Zainudin Hasan (brother)\n|children           = Futri Zulya Savitri <br /> Zita Anjani <br /> M. Farras Nugraha <br /> M. Rafi Haikal\n|alma_mater         = Krisanadwipayana University\n|occupation         = \n|profession         = Politician\n|religion           = [[Sunni Islam]]\n|signature          = \n|website            = http://www.zulhasan.com/\n|footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Zulkifli Hasan''' (born 17 May 1962 in Lampung) is an [[Indonesian people|Indonesian]] politician and has led the Islam-oriented [[National Mandate Party]] (Partai Amanat Nasional, PAN) since 1 March 2015. He was speaker of the [[People's Consultative Assembly|People's Consultative Assembly (MPR)]] from 2014 to 2019. He was Forestry Minister from 22 October 2009 to 1 October 2014.\n\n==Childhood and education==\nZulkifli Hasan was born to Hasan and Siti Zaenab, who were farmers in Pisang village in Penengahan, [[South Lampung Regency|South Lampung]]. In later life, he would claim to have experienced economic hardship as a child, saying he learnt to work hard by selling eggs produced on the farm. He attended a local elementary school from 1969 to 1975. At age 13, his father took him to Tanjungkarang (now called [[Bandar Lampung]]) to enroll him in junior high school level at the State Islamic Teachers Training School (PGAN), against the boy's wishes.<ref>{{cite news|title=Zulkifli Hasan: Man Jadda Wajada!|url=http://rilis.id/Zulkifli-Hasan-Man-Jadda-Wajada|accessdate=1 April 2018|publisher=RILISID|date=13 February 2017}}</ref> While attending PGAN, Zulkifli lived in a rented room in lodgings for boarders. He left PGAN in his fourth year at the school. He took an entrance exam for Madrasah Tsanawiah and passed. Without parental consent, he enrolled at Tandjungkarang State Senior High School. After four months, his father discovered he had switched schools and forced him to leave the high school.\n\nArmed with a little money from his mother, Zul moved to Jakarta. There, he attended State Senior High School 53 and graduated in 1982. In 1986, he enrolled at the Faculty of Economics at Krisnadwipayana University (Unkris) in Jakarta and financed his studies independently. In 2003, he graduated from PPM School of Management.<ref>{{cite news|title=Profil Zulkifli Hasan|url=https://www.viva.co.id/siapa/read/12-zulkifli-hasan|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=PT. Viva Media Baru}}</ref>\n\n== A self-made man ==\nHaving been raised in a farming family, Zulkifli was motivated to seek success beyond a rural environs. In a 2015 interview, he said his parents had wanted him to become like [[Buya Hamka]], an Islam-oriented journalist and author from Sumatra. \"But I refused. I wanted to migrate to Jakarta.\"\n\nArriving in Jakarta as a teenager without prior acquaintances or relatives, Zulkifli supported himself with jobs from washing taxis to selling drinks. He graduated from high school with the highest achievement in his class. He then tried his luck as a door-to-door salesman of pots and later attended college while doing business.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kuwado|first1=Fabian Januarius|title=Zulkifli Hasan Bicara Kesuksesannya sebagai \"Sales\" Panci dan Reformasi PAN|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2015/01/22/21413111/Zulkifli.Hasan.Bicara.Kesuksesannya.sebagai.Sales.Panci.dan.Reformasi.PAN|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Kompas.com|date=22 January 2015}}</ref> After exploring various areas of business, he began working for an ethnic Chinese businessman who sold home furnishings.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kisah Dua Menteri yang Sama-Sama Putra Lampung|url=https://www.jpnn.com/news/kisah-dua-menteri-yang-sama-sama-putra-lampung?page=2|accessdate=9 April 2018|publisher=JPNN.com|date=24 October 2009}}</ref>\n\nIn his later years, Zulkifli once visited Lembaga Pendidikan Insani (LPI), an educational institution whose operational costs came from Islamic donations. He told students there: \"If I ate eggs and could become a minister, then you who eat chicken should be able to become president.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Widjaya|first1=M. Akbar|title=Masa Kecil Menhut Zulkifli Hasan, Makan Sebutir Telur Dibagi Delapan|url=http://www.republika.co.id/berita/nasional/umum/11/10/21/lteug3-masa-kecil-menhut-zulkifli-hasan-makan-sebutir-telur-dibagi-delapan|accessdate=1 April 2018|publisher=Republika.co.id|date=21 October 2011}}</ref>\n\n''Bang'' (Brother) Zul, as he was known, remained close to the people of his hometown in Lampung and would present assistance in times of disaster.\n\n==Business career==\nPrior to becoming a politician, Zulkifli worked as a civil servant and then started his own businesses. His father had advised him not to be a follower but to be a leader, even if that meant starting from something small, so he quit the civil service.<ref>{{cite news|title=Zulkifli Hasan, Keluar dari PNS Jadi Pengusaha Sukses|url=https://finance.detik.com/sosok/d-1943289/zulkifli-hasan-keluar-dari-pns-jadi-pengusaha-sukses|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=detikFinance|date=17 June 2012}}</ref> His older brother, Herli Hasan, says Zulkifli left the civil service because the salary was low.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kisah Dua Menteri yang Sama-Sama Putra Lampung|url=https://www.jpnn.com/news/kisah-dua-menteri-yang-sama-sama-putra-lampung?page=2|accessdate=9 April 2018|publisher=JPNN.com|date=24 October 2009}}</ref>\n\nZulkifli's subsequent corporate positions included:\n\n* President Director of PT Batin Eka Perkasa (1988-2004), then Commissioner (2004-2005). A Jakarta-based company producing kitchen appliances under the Haneda brand-name; now run by Zulkifli's oldest daughter, Futri Zulya Savitri.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mengenal Futri Zulya Savitri, CEO PT Batin Eka Perkasa|url=http://indobisnis.indopos.co.id/read/2016/07/01/11333/Mengenal-Futri-Zulya-Savitri-CEO-PT-Batin-Eka-Perkasa-BEP|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=indopos.co.id|date=1 July 2016}}</ref>\n* President Director of PT Panamas Mitra Inti Lestari (1997-2004). A Bogor-based company selling home appliances and non-stick cookware.<ref>{{cite web|title=Panamas Mitra Inti Lestari PT|url=https://www.daftarperusahaan.com/bisnis/panamas-mitra-inti-lestari-pt|website=Daftarperusahaan.com|publisher=Daftarperusahaan.com|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n* President Director of PT Sarana Bina Insani, Jakarta (2000-2004). A travel bureau.<ref>{{cite news|title=Zul Sudah Diajak Bicara oleh SBY|url=https://issuu.com/tribunlampung/docs/tl1209|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Tribun Lampung|date=12 September 2009}}</ref>\n* Commissioner of PT Hudaya Safari Utama, Jakarta (2000-2006). A haj and umroh travel bureau.\n* Commissioner of [[PT Gudang Garam]], Jakarta (2006-2007).\n\n===Youth entrepreneurship===\nAfter starting his political career, he did not abandon his entrepreneurial interests. He became a motivator for young people and the wider community, particularly in Sumatra, to develop entrepreneurship and create new jobs. He encouraged rural youths to help advance Indonesia's future economic growth. In 2012, he supported a program of the National Mandate Party (PAN) that provided venture capital and training for young entrepreneurs in North Sumatra.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Suryana|first1=Dede|title=Jadi KEK, Sumut Harus Tingkatkan Wirausaha|url=https://economy.okezone.com/read/2012/05/06/320/624714/jadi-kek-sumut-harus-tingkatkan-wirausaha|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Okezone.com|date=6 May 2012}}</ref>\n\n== Early political career ==\nZulkifli was active in the [[Muhammadiyah]] mass Muslim organization, whose members were among the founders of the [[National Mandate Party]] (PAN) in 1998. His first political forays included chairing the Regional Board of Farmers and Fishermen of Lampung Province, serving as deputy chairman of Lampung Sai Community Society, and initiating the Lampung Youth Union in Jakarta. He chaired Muhammadiyah's Institute of Agricultural Laborers and Fishermen for Jakarta from 2000 to 2005. He chaired the Logistics Department of PAN's Central Board from 2000 to 2005.<ref>{{cite news|title=Keberuntungan Zulkifli Hasan menjadi ketua MPR|url=https://www.antaranews.com/berita/457660/keberuntungan-zulkifli-hasan-menjadi-ketua-mpr|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Antara|date=9 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nHe later became deputy chairman of PAN's faction in the House of Representatives, serving as a member of parliament from 2004 to 2009. He was a member of House Commission VI overseeing transportation and infrastructure. In July 2008, he was elected chairman of a special committee that questioned the government's policy to raise fuel prices.<ref>{{cite news|title=Zulkifli Hasan Terpilih Jadi Ketua Pansus Hak Angket BBM|url=https://otomotif.kompas.com/read/2008/07/09/14405974/Zulkifli.Hasan.Terpilih.Jadi.Ketua.Pansus.Hak.Angket.BBM|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Kompas.com|date=9 July 2008}}</ref>\n\nZulkifli was secretary general of PAN's Central Board for 2005 to 2010.<ref>{{cite news|title=Zulkifli Hasan Jadi Sekjen PAN 2005-2010|url=https://nasional.tempo.co/read/59387/zulkifli-hasan-jadi-sekjen-pan-2005-2010|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Tempo.co|date=11 April 2015}}</ref> On 8 October 2011, Zulkifli's oldest daughter Futri Zulya Savitri married PAN founder Amien Rais's third son, Ahmad Mumtaz Rais.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ketika Amien Rais dan Zulkifli Hasan Besanan|url=https://www.jpnn.com/news/ketika-amien-rais-dan-zulkifli-hasan-besanan|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=PT. JPG Multimedia|date=9 October 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Forestry Minister==\n[[File:Zulkifli Hasan.jpg|thumb|right|175px|Zulkifli as forestry minister, in 2013]]\nAfter President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono was re-elected for a second term in 2009, Zulkifli was appointed forestry minister on 21 October 2009. He said his priorities would be the development of production forests (HTI and HTR), reducing forest fires by 20% annually, combating illegal logging, streamlining of overlapping regulations of the central government and regencies for forest sites, and improving forest industry institutions. He also said he would resist temptations and pressure from businessmen and politicians putting themselves before the public interest. \u201cBut temptations are always there everywhere. It\u2019ll pose no problem to us if we just don\u2019t pay attention to them,\u201d he said.<ref>{{cite news|title=Zulkifli Hasan vows to live up to his political contract|url=http://www.pressreader.com/indonesia/the-jakarta-post/20091102/282956741238073|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=2 November 2009}}</ref> Indonesia's Corruption Eradication Commission (KPK) in 2012 declared the Forestry Ministry to be considered the country's most corrupt institution.<ref>{{cite news|title=Indonesia Struggles to Clean Up Corrupt Forestry Sector|url=http://jakartaglobe.id/news/indonesia-struggles-to-clean-up-corrupt-forestry-sector/|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Jakarta Globe|date=1 January 2014}}</ref> To support efforts to eradicate corruption, Zulkifli issued circular No.SE.2 / Menhut-II / 2012 on Gratification Reporting at the Ministry of Forestry. The circular encouraged staff at the ministry to report the gratuities they receive to their superiors to report to first echelon officials and the KPK.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Snowdon|first1=Karon|title=Forestry Ministry Signs an MoU With KPK|url=https://en.tempo.co/read/news/2013/05/21/055482221/Forestry-Ministry-Signs-an-MoU-With-KPK}}</ref> Zulkifli served as forestry minister until 1 October 2014.\n\n===Illegal forest operations===\nIn 2010, the Forestry Ministry promised to crack down on plantation companies operating without permits in Indonesia. In 2011, the ministry admitted hundreds of mining and plantation companies were operating in Central Kalimantan province without correct permits.<ref>{{cite news|title=Activists urge crackdown on 'forest mafia' networks|url=http://www.asia-pacific-solidarity.net/southeastasia/indonesia/netnews/2011/ind05v15.htm#Activists%20urge%20crackdown%20on%20'forest%20mafia'%20networks|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Jakarta Globe|date=3 February 2011}}</ref> Zulkifli said the problem was due to misinterpretations of regional autonomy legislation introduced in 2001. Elfian Effendi of Greenomics Indonesia said it was difficult for the minister to stop the offending companies because they have political links.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Snowdon|first1=Karon|title=Indonesia admits hundreds of companies without forestry permits|url=http://www.radioaustralia.net.au/international/2011-02-02/indonesia-admits-hundreds-of-companies-without-forestry-permits/224918|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=ABC Radio Australia|date=2 February 2011}}</ref> The Forestry Ministry promised to stop issuing new plantation and mine permits in the province and to cooperate with the Corruption Eradication Commission (KPK) to enforce the law.{{Citation needed|date=April 2018}}\n\n===Moratorium on new forest concessions===\nIn January 2011, Zulkifli announced the Forestry Ministry would implement a 2-year moratorium on the issuance of permits for the conversion of primary and peat forests.<ref>{{cite news|title=Govt to implement forest conversion moratorium in January|url=https://en.antaranews.com/news/66951/govt-to-implement-forest-conversion-moratorium-in-january|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Antara|date=13 January 2011}}</ref> Conservationists noted that on the eve of the logging moratorium, the ministry issued 2.9 million hectares of new plantation concessions to 44 firms.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lang|first1=Chris|title=On the eve of the logging moratorium, Indonesia\u2019s Ministry of Forestry issued almost three million hectares of concessions|url=http://www.redd-monitor.org/2011/01/26/on-the-eve-of-the-logging-moratorium-indonesias-ministry-of-forestry-issued-almost-three-million-hectares-of-concessions/|website=REDD-Monitor|publisher=Wordpress|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref> On 20 May 2011, President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono signed a presidential decree putting the two-year moratorium into effect. The decree covered from 64 million to 72 million hectares of primary forest and peatland.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Stolle|first1=Fred|title=Indonesia\u2019s Ambitious Forest Moratorium Moves Forward|url=http://www.wri.org/blog/2011/06/indonesia%E2%80%99s-ambitious-forest-moratorium-moves-forward|website=World Resources Institute|publisher=World Resources Institute|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Allegation of state losses===\nIn May 2013, the Indonesian Forum for Budget Transparency (Fitra) claimed data from the State Audit Agency (BPK) showed the Forestry Ministry had lost or misappropriated Rp 7.1 trillion ($731 million) in 2012. Zulkifli responded by saying the data and description of \u201closses\u201d were inaccurate. He said the actual figure was Rp 6.2 trillion in non-tax revenue the ministry has been unable to collect since 2002. \u201cWe\u2019re continuing to collect on those payments, both at the regional level and at the central level, and to date we\u2019ve whittled down the outstanding amount to just Rp 2.1 trillion,\u201d he said.<ref>{{cite news|title=Indonesian Ministers Deny Claims They Have Lost 8.3t Rupiah|url=http://jakartaglobe.id/news/indonesian-ministers-deny-claims-they-have-lost-8-3t-rupiah/|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Jakarta Globe|date=3 May 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Interview by Harrison Ford===\nOn 9 September 2013, Zulkifli was interviewed by [[Harrison Ford]] for part of a documentary series on climate change and the environment. Presidential adviser Andi Arief complained Ford had attacked the minister with rude questions. He accused Ford and his crew of \u201charassing state institutions\u201d and threatened to deport him.\n\nZulkifli said Ford was emotional because he wanted illegal loggers swiftly arrested at [[Tesso Nilo National Park|Tesso Nilo]] National Park in Sumatra. The minister said Ford did not give him sufficient time to explain the difficulties of catching those who violate forestry laws. He lamented they had not rehearsed the interview before filming commenced.<ref>{{cite news|title=FM bemoans Harrison Ford's attitude|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2013/09/09/fm-bemoans-harrison-ford-s-attitude.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=9 September 2013}}</ref> Ford was making part of a series on climate change called ''[[Years of Living Dangerously]]'' for US television network [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Harrison Ford shocks Indonesian minister with heated climate interview|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2013-09-10/indonesian-minister-shocked-at-harrison-ford-climate-interview/4949316|accessdate=3 April 2018|agency=AFP|publisher=ABC News|date=11 September 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Hazardous smoke haze===\nDuring Zulkifli's tenure as forestry minister, forests in Sumatra and Kalimantan were burned to clear land for plantations, causing hazardous haze that reached neighboring Singapore and Malaysia. In 2013, Kuntoro Mangkusubroto, the head of Indonesia's presidential working unit for development supervision and control, said many fires were on land owned by Asia Pulp and Paper (APP) and Asia Pacific Resources International Limited. Zulkifli said there was no strong evidence against the two companies.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lim|first1=Leonard|title=MFA seeks answers from Jakarta to conflicting views on whether Singapore firms caused haze|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/mfa-seeks-answers-from-jakarta-to-conflicting-views-on-whether-singapore-firms-caused-haze|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=The Straits Times|date=25 June 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2013, Zulkifli blamed the severity of the haze on a five-year weather cycle. \"Every five years, the weather becomes extremely dry. The wind is also much stronger and moves in a circular motion. So, when there is burning, fire spreads very quickly... Due to the dry season, it takes time for firefighters to locate the water sources. By the time water is irrigated to the hot spots, the fire would have spread.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lim|first1=Joyce|title=Severity of haze 'due to 5-year cycle' of dry weather|url=http://www.asiaone.com/health/severity-haze-due-5-year-cycle-dry-weather|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=The Straits Times|date=28 June 2013}}</ref> Responding to allegations that plantation and forestry companies were responsible for the fires, Zulkifli was quoted by [[Tempo Magazine (Indonesia)|''Tempo'' magazine]] as saying the companies must be defended because they pay taxes.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cahyadi|first1=Firdaus|title=When People's Safety are Sacrificed to Defend Companies|url=https://en.tempo.co/read/news/2013/07/07/080494143/When-Peoples-Safety-are-Sacrificed-to-Defend-Companies|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Tempo.co|date=7 July 2013}}</ref> He said 14 people had been arrested on suspicion of starting fires, 11 of them linked to companies and three of them smallholders. \"If proven guilty they could be jailed for five years and have their permits revoked,\" he said.<ref>{{cite news|title=Indonesia allocates Rp100 billion to overcome forest fires|url=https://en.antaranews.com/news/89602/indonesia-allocates-rp100-billion-to-overcome-forest-fires|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Antara|date=28 June 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2014, Zulkifli supported calls by the National Police and Indonesian Military for the shooting of people found burning forests if they resist arrest. He acknowledged the people responsible for forest fires were seeking to open up new land for oil palm plantations.<ref>{{cite news|title=Forestry Minister Echoes Calls for Strict Action on Haze Issue|url=http://jakartaglobe.id/news/forestry-minister-echoes-calls-strict-action-haze-issue/|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Jakarta Globe|date=18 March 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, anti-haze activist Syahrul Fitra accused Zulkifli of allowing corporations to burn forests and causing the haze crisis. He claimed Zulkifli had allegedly given permission for the burning of over 1.3 million hectares of forests be used for plantations. He said law enforcers should arrest any officials responsible for the haze and called for an investigation into possible corruption in the issuance of permits. Zulkifli denied any wrongdoing.<ref>{{cite news|title=Former Indonesian Forestry Minister blamed by activist for haze crisis|url=http://www.todayonline.com/world/asia/former-indonesian-forestry-minister-blamed-activist-haze-crisis|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Mediacorp Press Ltd|date=1 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Riau forestry corruption case===\nIn August 2014, Zulkifli visited [[Riau]] province and encouraged proposals to change the status of forest land owned by locals so it could become part of 1,638,249 hectares allowed by the [[Indonesian Ministry of Forestry|Forestry Ministry]] for conversion into non-forest land.\n\nRiau governor Annas Ma'mun's administration responded by sending a proposal to Zulkifli, who gave his approval to some of the areas. Annas later revised the proposal, adding some land owned by palm-oil businessman Gulat Manurung, who paid a bribe of S$156,000 and Rp 500 million. Annas later stated Zulkifli had approved and issued the conversion permit.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Budiari|first1=Indra|title=MPR speaker faces more questions from KPK|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2014/11/13/mpr-speaker-faces-more-questions-kpk.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=13 November 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 November 2014, Zulkifli was questioned as a witness by the [[Corruption Eradication Commission]] (KPK) in the case against Annas. Zulkifli denied approving the permit. Annas said he had been on his way to meet with Zulkifli when he was arrested by the KPK in a sting operation in September 2014.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Budiari|first1=Indra|title=Governor piles more allegations on Zulkifli|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2014/11/19/governor-piles-more-allegations-zulkifli.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=19 November 2014}}</ref>\n\nTestifying at Annas's corruption trial in April 2015, Zulkifli admitted he had met with the director of PT Duta Palma, Surya Darmadi, to discuss a forest clearing permit. Surya was linked to the case by Gulat, who said he helped PT Duta Palma to meet with Annas to enable the company to convert 18,000 hectares of land.<ref>{{cite news|last1=S.|first1=Iqbal T. Lazuardi|title=Zulkifli Hasan Admits Meeting Company CEO|publisher=Tempo.co|date=8 April 2015}}</ref> Gulat was in February 2015 sentenced to three years in jail.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Movanita|first1=Ambaranie Nadia Kemala|title=Suap Gubernur Riau Rp 2 Miliar, Gulat Manurung Divonis Tiga Tahun Penjara|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2015/06/25/court-sentences-riau-governor-6-years-prison-corrupt.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Kompas.com|date=23 February 2015}}</ref> Annas was in June 2015 sentenced to six years in jail.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dipa|first1=Arya|title=Court sentences Riau governor to 6 years in prison for corrupt|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2015/06/25/court-sentences-riau-governor-6-years-prison-corrupt.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jajkarta Post|date=25 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Bogor land conversion case===\nZulkifli was questioned by the KPK on 11 November 2014 over the illegal issuance of a land conversion permit for a luxury housing project in [[Bogor Regency|Bogor]], [[West Java]]. The project was developed by property firm [[Sentul City, Indonesia|PT Sentul City]]. Former Bogor regent Rachmat Yasin received Rp 4.5 billion in bribes from Sentul City president director Kwee Cahyadi Kumala, who is president commissioner of property company PT Bukit Jonggol Asri (BJA), the main shareholder of Sentul City. KPK in December 2014 raided the Forestry Ministry to seize evidence. Zulkifli denied any wrongdoing. The Forestry Ministry's director general for planning, Bambang Supijanto, said Zulkifli had rejected BJA's proposal to convert nearly 3,000 acres of forest area for housing projects in Bogor because it lacked some requirements.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Halim|first1=Haeril|title=KPK raids ministry's office in land-conversion case|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2014/12/17/kpk-raids-ministry-s-office-land-conversion-case.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=17 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Forest smallholdings and education===\nZulkifli sought to improve the performance and image of the Forestry Ministry through two programs: one targeting the growth of agriculture through smallholdings in forest areas, and the other promoting environmental education. The first was the simplification of the application procedure for the development of smallholdings under the Community Nursery (''Kebun Bibit Rakyat'', KBR) scheme, introduced in 2010 and simplified in 2011.<ref>{{cite news |title=Prosedur Kebun Bibit Rakyat Dipermudah |url=https://ekonomi.kompas.com/read/2011/03/16/0352377/prosedur.kebun.bibit.rakyat.dipermudah |accessdate=6 August 2018 |publisher=Kompas Cyber Media |date=16 March 2011}}</ref> The second is the Forest Education program, which involves students visiting selected forest areas and planting trees.{{Citation needed|date=August 2018}}\n\n===Flurry of decrees===\nConservation groups have alleged that after Joko Widodo had won Indonesia\u2019s presidential election in July 2014, Zulkifli realized he would not retain his cabinet position because PAN was not part of the incoming ruling coalition, so he therefore started issuing more ministerial decrees, right up to his final week in office, when 100 decrees were signed. Many of the decrees granted new concessions for timber and logging companies, or allowed forest land to be used by oil palm plantation companies. Much of the land in question is in Papua province.<ref>{{cite web|title=September 29th 2014, a terrible day for Papua\u2019s forests|url=https://awasmifee.potager.org/?p=1600|website=awasMIFEE!|publisher=awasMIFEE!|accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref> Greenomics Indonesia said Zulkfli, during his tenure as minister, granted permits for 1.64 million acres of forest land to be used for farming, including for oil palm plantations.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hendartyo|first1=Muhammad|title=Greenomics says PAN Cadre Granted More Land Permits Than Jokowi|url=https://en.tempo.co/read/news/2018/03/22/055916893/Greenomics-says-PAN-Cadre-Granted-More-Land-Permits-Than-Jokowi|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Tempo.co|date=22 March 2018}}</ref> Zulkifli in March 2018 defended his action, saying Papua needed more land for sugar cultivation.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Novaria|first1=Astri|title=Respon Zulkifli Hasan Jawab Tudingan Greenomics|url=http://mediaindonesia.com/read/detail/151069-respon-zulkifli-hasan-jawab-tudingan-greenomics|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Media Indonesia|date=23 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==MPR Speaker==\n[[File:Ali Larijani meeting with Indonesian parliament chairman Zulkifli Hasan 02.jpg|thumb|right|175px|Zulkifli in parlament, December 2016]]\nOn 8 October 2014, Zulkifli was sworn in as speaker of the People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) for the 2014-2019 period. His appointment was supported by [[Prabowo Subianto]]'s Red-and-White Coalition following Prabowo's loss of the [[2014 Indonesian presidential election|2014 presidential election]] to [[Joko Widodo|Joko \"Jokowi\" Widodo]]. Although PAN was then a member of the opposition coalition, Zulkifli promised to uphold the interests of all Indonesians and not just those of his political supporters. Jokowi's coalition had wanted [[Oesman Sapta Odang]] as MPR speaker, but Zulkifli defeated Oesman by 347 to 330 votes.<ref>{{cite news|title=Zulkifli Hasan inaugurated as new speaker of People's Consultative Assembly|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2014/10/08/zulkifli-hasan-inaugurated-new-speaker-people-s-consultative-assembly.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=8 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nOne of Zulkifli's first tasks as MPR speaker was to lead the inauguration ceremony of Indonesia's seventh president, Joko Widodo, on 20 October 2014. He was credited for ensuring the event was attended by the losing presidential candidate Prabowo Subianto, who had vigorously rejected the election result.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hariyadi|first1=Yoseph|title=Jokowi inaugurated as Indonesia's new president|url=https://en.antaranews.com/news/96163/jokowi-inaugurated-as-indonesias-new-president|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=20 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 December 2014, Zulkifli said protests against then-Jakarta governor [[Basuki Tjahaja Purnama]], better known as Ahok, on the basis of his religion and race were unacceptable. Ahok, a Christian of Chinese ethnicity, faced opposition from conservative Muslim groups. \"I strongly protest those who protest against Ahok because he's ethnic Chinese or because of his religion. If you want to criticize, go ahead, but do not make it about ethnicity, religion or race, as we are united in diversity,\" he said.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ketua MPR: Tak Boleh Ada yang Protes Ahok Karena Etnis dan Agamanya|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-2784784/ketua-mpr-tak-boleh-ada-yang-protes-ahok-karena-etnis-dan-agamanya|accessdate=5 April 2018|publisher=detikcom|date=22 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Stance on alcohol and drugs===\nIn May 2016, Zulkifli called for tighter regulations on the sale of alcohol, saying it has negative social consequences, including death and crimes of obscenity.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Zulfikar|first1=Muhammad|title=Zulkifli Hasan: Peredaran Miras di Indonesia Harus Diatur|url=http://www.tribunnews.com/mpr-ri/2016/05/27/zulkifli-hasan-peredaran-miras-di-indonesia-harus-diatur|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Tribunnews.com|date=27 May 2016}}</ref> Indonesia already bans the sale of alcohol to minors.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wahyuningsih|first1=Merry|title=Tak Boleh Minum Bir Sebelum Umur 21 Tahun|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/gaya-hidup/20141031121011-255-9076/tak-boleh-minum-bir-sebelum-umur-21-tahun|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=CNN Indonesia|date=31 October 2014}}</ref> In January 2018, Zulkifli claimed eight parties in the national parliament were in favor of open alcohol sales at small shops. He said alcoholic drinks should be rejected firmly.<ref>{{cite news|title=Delapan Fraksi Setujui Penjualan Miras Secara Bebas|url=https://www.jawapos.com/read/2018/01/20/182792/delapan-fraksi-setujui-penjualan-miras-secara-bebas|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=PT Jawa Pos Grup Multimedia|date=20 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2016, Zulkifli called for smoking to be banned as it contributes to \"ignorance and poverty\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Aco|first1=Hasanudin|title=Zulkifli Hasan: Stop Merokok!|url=http://www.tribunnews.com/nasional/2016/02/16/zulkifli-hasan-stop-merokok|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=TRIBUNnews.com|date=February 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2018, Zulkifli said drug traffickers should be shot dead, while drug users should be rehabilitated rather than imprisoned, as most of Indonesia's prison inmates are drug offenders.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tegas!! Zulkifli Hasan Sebut Bandar Narkoba Ditembak Mati|url=http://www.inikata.com/tegas-zulkifli-hasan-sebut-bandar-narkoba-ditembak-mati/|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=PT. Indo Network Intermedia|date=12 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Opposition to LGBT===\nIn March 2016, Zulkifli said the lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender (LGBT) movement should have no place in Indonesia, but he warned against violence and discrimination. \"As a movement, the existence of LGBT must be opposed. We must limit its room to move. However, as individual people, they must be protected like any other citizen,\" he said.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Nurbinato|first1=Bambang|title=More political leaders speak out against LGBT|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2016/03/04/more-political-leaders-speak-out-against-lgbt.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=21 March 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2018, Zulkifli falsely claimed five parties in the House of Representatives were supporting a bill to legalize same-sex marriage. His statement was refuted by House speaker [[Bambang Soesatyo]],<ref>{{cite news|last1=La Batu|first1=Safrin|title=MPR speaker\u2019s remarks on LGBT spark controversy|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2018/01/23/mpr-speaker-s-remarks-lgbt-spark-controversy.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=23 January 2018}}</ref> and prompted other major parties to affirm their opposition to gay rights.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Knight|first1=Kyle|title=Why criminalizing LGBT relationships is misguided|url=http://www.atimes.com/criminalising-lgbt-relations-indonesia-preposterous/|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Asia Times|date=14 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Protecting LGBTs|url=https://en.tempo.co/read/news/2018/02/06/314915509/Protecting-LGBTs|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Tempo.co|date=6 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Chairman of PAN==\nPAN held a congress in Bali over 28 February to 2 March 2015 to choose a chairman for the 2015-2020 period. Among those considered contenders were Zulkifli, then-incumbent chairman Hatta Rajasa and deputy chairman Dradjad Wibowo.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tiga Nama Calon Ketua Umum PAN|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2014/12/18/09333521/Tiga.Nama.Calon.Ketua.Umum.PAN|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Komps.com|date=18 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nZulkifli announced his candidacy on 19 January 2015 in Surabaya. The Chairman of PAN's Youth Front Advisory Council, Hanafi Rais, said Zulkfli wanted the party to focus on defending the interests of the people, as well as giving local party officials full authority in determining regional leadership boards, and improving the performances of regional heads.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Stefanie|first1=Christie|title=Deklarasi Ketua Umum PAN, Zulkifli Hasan Bawa 4 Gagasan|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20150121121055-32-26195/deklarasi-ketua-umum-pan-zulkifli-hasan-bawa-4-gagasan|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=CNN Indonesia|date=21 January 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 March 2015, Zulkifli was narrowly elected PAN chairman, receiving 292 votes, while Hatta Rajasa received 286 votes.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Aritonang|first1=Margareth S.|title=MPR speaker elected new PAN chief|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2015/03/02/mpr-speaker-elected-new-pan-chief.html|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=The Jakarta Post|date=2 March 2015}}</ref> After his election, Zulkifli insisted PAN would remain part of Prabowo Subianto's opposition coalition.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sihaloho|first1=Markus Junianto|title=PAN Will Remain in Opposition, New Chairman Zulkifli Says|url=http://jakartaglobe.id/news/pan-will-remain-opposition-new-chairman-zulkifli-says/|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Jakarta Globe|date=2 March 2015}}</ref> On 2 September 2015, Zulkifli announced PAN was switching its allegiance to Jokowi's ruling coalition in order to help the government's programs succeed.<ref>{{cite news|title=PAN Officially Switches Sides, Joins Jokowi's Coalition|url=http://jakartaglobe.id/news/pan-officially-switches-sides-joins-jokowis-coalition/|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=Jakarta Globe|date=2 September 2015}}</ref> On 9 August 2018, Zulkifli shifted PAN's allegiance back to Prabowo amid allegations that Prabowo's running mate for the 2019 presidential election, Sandiaga Uno, had paid Rp 500 billion to PAN in order to secure his nomination. PAN denied the allegation.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Saputro |first1=Febrianto Adi |title=PAN actually wants Anies Baswedan to run with Prabowo |url=https://www.republika.co.id/berita/en/national-politics/18/08/23/pdxafc414-pan-actually-wants-anies-baswedan-to-run-with-prabowo |accessdate=25 August 2018 |publisher=Republika.co.id |date=24 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=PAN, PKS deny getting Rp 500b to let Sandiaga become VP candidate |url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2018/08/09/pan-pks-deny-getting-rp-500b-to-let-sandiaga-become-vp-candidate.html |accessdate=25 August 2018 |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=9 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Money politics===\nIn February 2017, Zulkifli urged Indonesians to avoid all forms of money politics in regional elections. \u201cThe sovereignty and power are fully in the hands of the people. Do not trade it for money or staple foods,\u201d he said.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sihaloho|first1=Markus Junianto|title=MPR Speaker Zulkifli Hasan Calls on Public to Avoid Money Politics in Regional Elections|url=http://jakartaglobe.id/news/mpr-speaker-zulkifli-hasan-calls-on-public-to-avoid-money-politics-in-regional-elections/|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Jakarta Globe|date=14 February 2017}}</ref> On 6 March 2018, Zulkifli was filmed giving money to women in a public transport vehicle at a market in [[Muara Enim Regency|Muara Enim]] in [[South Sumatra]] province, ahead of the election for the regent of Muara Enim. He was accompanied at the market by regency head candidate Syamsul Bahri, who is supported by PAN.<ref>{{cite news|title=Adriansyah Laporkan Balik Cabub Syamsul Bahri Ke Polres Muara Enim|url=http://www.palugadanews.com/2018/03/adriansyah-laporkan-balik-cabub-syamsul-bahri-ke-polres-muara-enim/|accessdate=7 April 2018|publisher=Palugadanews.com|date=5 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Inge|first1=Nefri|title=PAN Bantah Zulkifli Hasan Lakukan Politik Uang di Pilkada Muara Enim|url=http://www.liputan6.com/pilkada/read/3373367/pan-bantah-zulkifli-hasan-lakukan-politik-uang-di-pilkada-muara-enim|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Liputan6.com|date=14 March 2018}}</ref> The Election Supervisory Agency (Panwaslu) of Muara Enim conducted an investigation and attempted to summon Zulkifli for questioning but he was too busy to attend.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Inge|first1=Nefri|title=Terekam Bagi-Bagi Duit, Zulkifli Hasan Akan Diperiksa Panwas Muara Enim|url=http://www.liputan6.com/pilkada/read/3370498/terekam-bagi-bagi-duit-zulkifli-hasan-akan-diperiksa-panwas-muara-enim|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Liputan6.com|date=14 March 2018}}</ref> PAN officials denied the handing out of money in the presence of the candidate constituted money politics, arguing Syamsul Bahri's presence was his own initiative.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Inge|first1=Nefri|title=PAN Bantah Zulkifli Hasan Lakukan Politik Uang di Pilkada Muara Enim|url=http://www.liputan6.com/pilkada/read/3373367/pan-bantah-zulkifli-hasan-lakukan-politik-uang-di-pilkada-muara-enim|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Liputan6.com|date=14 March 2018}}</ref> Panwaslu later concluded Zulkifli had not been trying to influence voters to choose a particular candidate.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Inge|first1=Nefri|title=Alasan Panwas Muara Enim Bebaskan Zulkifli Hasan|url=http://www.liputan6.com/pilkada/read/3382311/alasan-panwas-muara-enim-bebaskan-zulkifli-hasan|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Liputan6.com|date=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Presidential ambition===\nIn February 2018, Zulkifli said he would be ready to contest Indonesia's [[2019 Indonesian presidential election|2019 presidential election]] if he is nominated.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Triansyah|first1=Isra|title=Zulkifli Hasan Siap Maju Capres jika Diusung PAN|url=https://nasional.sindonews.com/read/1283700/12/zulkifli-hasan-siap-maju-capres-jika-diusung-pan-1519128456|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=SINDOnews.com|date=20 February 2018}}</ref> He later acknowledged any presidential nominee would likely require the backing of a coalition of parties.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Purbaya|first1=Angling Adhitya|title=Zulkifli Perhitungkan Syarat Kursi 20% Untuk Ikut Pilpres|url=https://news.detik.com/berita-jawa-tengah/d-3943561/zulkifli-perhitungkan-syarat-kursi-20-untuk-ikut-pilpres|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=detikcom|date=29 March 2018}}</ref> In April 2018, he said he would be PAN's presidential candidate, despite speculation the party might choose former military commander [[Gatot Nurmantyo]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bayhaqi|first1=Ahda|title=Zulkifli Hasan sebut PAN tak akan usung Gatot di Pilpres 2019|url=https://www.merdeka.com/politik/zulkifli-hasan-sebut-pan-tak-akan-usung-gatot-di-pilpres-2019.html|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Merdeka.com|date=4 April 2018}}</ref> PAN ended up supporting Prabowo Subianto for the 2019 presidential election.<ref>{{cite news |title=Zulkifli Hasan Reveals Prabowo-Sandiaga Campaign Team |url=https://en.tempo.co/read/news/2018/08/18/055920916/Zulkifli-Hasan-Reveals-Prabowo-Sandiaga-Campaign-Team |accessdate=25 August 2018 |publisher=Tempo.co |date=18 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2020 chair fight===\nOn 11 February 2020, Zulkifli was re-elected as PAN leader for another five-year period at a congress marred by violence.<ref>{{cite news |title=Zulkifli Reelected PAN Chairman in Chaotic Congress |url=https://jakartaglobe.id/news/zulkifli-reelected-pan-chairman-in-chaotic-congress |accessdate=14 February 2020 |publisher=Jakarta Globe |date=12 February 2020}}</ref> At least 10 people were injured when supporters of Zulkifli and his challenger Mulfachri Harahap threw chairs at each other.<ref>{{cite news |title=At least 10 injured in violent dispute during second day of PAN congress |url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/02/12/at-least-10-injured-in-violent-dispute-during-second-day-of-pan-congress.html |accessdate=14 February 2020 |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=12 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life and family==\nZulkifli is married to Soraya and they have four children: Futri Zulya Savitri, Zita Anjani, Farras Nugraha and Rafi Haikal.\n\nOldest daughter Futri Zulya Savitri studied in Australia, married a son of Amien Rais and runs a family business making household and kitchen appliances.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Suryadi|first1=Dede|title=Liku-liku Futri Membenahi Haneda|url=https://swa.co.id/swa/profile/profile-entrepreneur/liku-liku-futri-membenahi-haneda|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=SWA Online Magazine|date=11 February 2017}}</ref>\n\nOldest son, Farras Nugraha, studied in the UK and is now a businessman. In September 2017, Farras married Milka Anisya Norosiya. Among their wedding guests were military commander General [[Gatot Nurmantyo]] and senior politicians Oesman Sapta Odang, Amien Rais, [[Hidayat Nur Wahid]], [[Aburizal Bakrie]] and [[Akbar Tandjung]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Laksana|first1=Bisma  Alief|title=Panglima TNI Hingga Ketua DPD Jadi Saksi Nikah Putra Zulkifli Hasan|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/3655732/panglima-tni-hingga-ketua-dpd-jadi-saksi-nikah-putra-zulkifli-hasan|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=detikcom|date=24 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nZulkifli's second daughter, Zita Anjani, studied in London and in 2015 opened an early learning school called Kids Republic. His youngest child, Rafi Haikal, chose to study architecture in New York.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Septianto|first1=Bayu|title=Dari Kursi Bisnis ke MPR, Zulkifli Hasan Ingin Bangun Sekolah di Masa Tua|url=https://news.okezone.com/read/2018/01/20/337/1847853/dari-kursi-bisnis-ke-mpr-zulkifli-hasan-ingin-bangun-sekolah-di-masa-tua|accessdate=4 April 2018|publisher=Okezone News|date=20 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Brothers===\nZulkifli has four brothers, including three who also became politicians: Zainudin Hasan (born 1965),  Hazizi (1976) and [[Helmi Hasan]] (1979). The oldest brother in the family is Herli Hasan.\n\nHelmi Hasan, who became mayor of Bengkulu in 2013, viewed Zulkifli not only as an older brother but also as a parent to be obeyed and respected.<ref>{{cite news|title=Dibalik \"Insya Allah\" Helmi Hasan|url=http://bengkuluekspress.com/dibalik-insya-allah-helmi-hasan/|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Bengkuluekspress.com|date=21 January 2013}}</ref> Zulkifli, Helmi and Zainudin founded Insan Cendikia Kalianda Lampung Indonesia Foundation, which built a free school for children from poor families in Lampung.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Supriyadi|first1=Eko|title=Zulkifli Hasan Tinjau SMA Kebangsaan di Lampung|url=http://www.republika.co.id/berita/mpr-ri/berita-mpr/16/03/17/o46sy3254-zulkifli-hasan-tinjau-sma-kebangsaan-di-lampung|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=republika.co.id|date=17 March 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2015, Helmi Hasan was declared a suspect by Bengkulu Attorney General's Office for allegedly embezzling Rp 11.4 billion ($870,000) of social aid from the city's 2012-2013 budget.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bengkulu Mayor Named Corruption Suspect|url=http://jakartaglobe.id/news/bengkulu-mayor-named-corruption-suspect/|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Jakarta Globe|date=18 March 2015}}</ref> Helmi filed a pre-trial motion, which was accepted on 9 September 2015 by Bengkulu City State Court, so he did not stand trial.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Supriatin|title=Pengadilan batalkan status tersangka wali kota Bengkulu Helmi Hasan|url=https://www.merdeka.com/peristiwa/pn-bengkulu-batalkan-status-tersangka-wali-kota-bengkulu-helmi-hasan.html|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Merdeka.com|date=10 September 2015}}</ref> The former head of Bengkulu City's Office for Management of Regional Revenue, Finance and Assets, M. Sofyan, in September 2017 testified Bengkulu Regional Secretary, Marjon, had ordered him to release Rp 500 million in state funds to pay for the success of Helmi's pre-trial motion.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rahmadani|first1=Yetti|title=Terkuak, Rp 500 Juta Selamatkan Helmi Hasan Dari Praperadilan Bansos|url=http://www.rmolbengkulu.com/read/2017/09/06/4705/Terkuak,-Rp-500-Juta-Selamatkan-Helmi-Hasan-Dari-Praperadilan-Bansos-|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Rakyat Merdeka Online|date=6 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2015, Zainudin Hasan was elected regent of South Lampung regency for the 2016-2021 period.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mualifah|first1=Siti|title=Zainuddin-Nanang Menangi Pilkada Lampung Selatan Versi KPU|url=http://www.jejamo.com/zainuddin-nanang-menangi-pilkada-lampung-selatan-versi-kpu.html|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=jejamo.com|date=16 December 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2017, police in Bandar Lampung city named a Hazizi a fraud suspect for allegedly asking a contractor to pay a bribe of Rp 515 million in order to obtain a contract for infrastructure projects worth Rp 3.5 billion in South Lampung regency, where his brother Zainudin is regent.<ref>{{cite news|title=Pernah Tersangka Penipuan Proyek Hazizi mundur dari dewan|url=https://be1lampung.com/propinsi/pernah-tersangka-penipuan-proyek|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=PT Besatu Lampung Media|date=14 May 2017}}</ref> The contractor, Syahruddin, died in May 2016 without ever receiving the allegedly promised contract. His eldest son later reported Hazizi to police.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rinando|first1=Romi|title=Hazizi, Adik Ketua MPR Zulkifli Hasan Ditetapkan Tersangka Kasus Dugaan Penipuan Proyek|url=http://lampung.tribunnews.com/2017/02/10/hazizi-adik-ketua-mpr-zulkifli-hasan-ditetapkan-tersangka-kasus-dugaan-penipuan-proyek|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Tribun Lampung|date=10 February 2017}}</ref> In May 2017, Hazizi resigned from his seat in Lampung legislative assembly \"for no specific reason\" apart from \"wanting to concentrate on worship\", according to one of his colleagues in PAN.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Yulianto|first1=Beni|title=Adik Kandung Ketua MPR Mengundurkan Diri dari DPRD Lampung|url=http://lampung.tribunnews.com/2017/05/09/adik-kandung-ketua-mpr-mengundurkan-diri-dari-dprd-lampung|accessdate=8 April 2018|publisher=Tribun Lampung|date=9 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Martial arts===\nZulkifli is a practitioner of [[kyokushin]], a type of full contact karate. He served as chairman of the Board of Supervisors of Kyokushinkan International Indonesia. In June 2010, he received an honorary black belt from the supreme leader of Kyokushin International.<ref>{{cite web|title=Honorary Black-Belt submission to H. Zulkifli Hasan SE. MM.|url=http://www.kyokushinkan-indonesia.org/eng/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=36&Itemid=38|website=Kyokushinkan Indonesia|publisher=Kyokushinkan Indonesia|accessdate=9 April 2018}}</ref> Zulkifli is also a practitioner of [[Tarung Derajat]], a full body contact Indonesian mixed martial art. He was chairman of the Tarung Derajat Sports Family from 2010-2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tarung Derajat Tampil di SEA Games 2011|url=https://sport.tempo.co/read/252294/tarung-derajat-tampil-di-sea-games-2011|accessdate=9 April 2018|agency=Tempo.co|date=2 June 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Honors==\nOn 26 July 2007, Jakarta's PPM School of Management presented Zulkifli with the Kadarman Award, which is given to successful alumni.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sekjen DPP PAN Zulkifli Hasan Terima Kadarman Award|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/809996/sekjen-dpp-pan-zulkifli-hasan-terima-kadarman-award?nd771104bcj=|accessdate=3 April 2018|publisher=detikcom|date=26 July 2007}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 July 2010, Zulkifli received a nobility title from Solo Palace in Central Java. He was bestowed the title of Kanjeng Pangeran (Prince) Noto Wononagoro for his efforts to preserve Javanese culture.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Amri |first1=Arfi Bambani |title=Jupe dan Zulkifli Hasan Dapat Gelar Bangsawan |url=https://www.viva.co.id/berita/nasional/163297-jupe-dan-zulkifli-hasan-dapat-gelar-bangsawan |accessdate=6 August 2018 |publisher=PT Viva Media Baru |date=8 July 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2014, President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono presented Zulkifli with the Bintang Jasa Mahaputra Adipradana medal for his services to the country.<ref>{{cite web|title=Menhut Menerima Bintang Jasa Mahaputra Adipradana|url=http://www.forda-mof.org/index.php/berita/post/1795|website=Ministry of Environment and Forestry Republic of Indonesia|publisher=Badan litbang & Inovasi Kementerian Lingkungan Hidup & Kehutanan|accessdate=8 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 November 2017, Zulkifli was awarded the title of Pangeran Kerta Jaya Alam Nata from an organization of residents of [[Lubuklinggau]] in  South Sumatra. The title, which means the leader of the people who carries out the mandate, was presented to him for \"consistently defending the people\". Organizers said Zulkifli is the only person to receive the title.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tambak |first1=Ruslan |title=Zulkifli Hasan Satu-satunya Yang Diberi Gelar Pangeran Kerta Jaya Alam Nata |url=https://www.rmol.co/read/2017/11/15/314583/Zulkifli-Hasan-Satu-satunya-Yang-Diberi-Gelar-Pangeran-Kerta-Jaya-Alam-Nata- |accessdate=6 August 2018 |publisher=Rakyat Merdeka Online |date=15 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Ministry of Forestry (Indonesia)|Ministry of Forestry of the Republic of Indonesia]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://zulkiflihasan.info/ Official website]\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{succession box| title=[[Forestry minister]] of [[Indonesia]] | before=[[Malam Sambat Kaban]] | after=[[Chairul Tanjung]]| years=2009\u20132014}} \n{{s-bef|before=[[Sidarto Danusubroto]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Speaker of the People's Consultative Assembly|years=2014\u20132019}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Bambang Soesatyo]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Leaders of Indonesian political parties}}\n\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hasan, Zulk}}\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Lampung]]\n[[Category:Government ministers 